1 /**
  2  * @fileOverview This file has functions related to documenting JavaScript.
  3  * @author <a href="mailto:dana.henkens@gmail.com">Dana Henkens</a>
  4  * @version 1.0
  5  */
  6 /**
  7  * @namespace Main module and Namespace declaration
  8  * @requires GeForMT.GestureModel
  9  * @requires GeForMT.Parser
 10  * @requires GeForMT.SelectorEngine
 11  * @requires GeForMT.Observation
 12  * @requires GeForMT.GestureRecognizer
 13  * @requires GeForMT.TemplateBuilder
 14  * @requires GeForMT.Types
 15  * @requires Sizzle
 16  * @requires PEG.GeneratedGeForMTParser
 17  */
 18 var GeForMT = (function(){
 19 
 20     /**
 21      * Gesture model module.
 22      * @type GeForMT.GestureModel
 23      * @default GeForMT.GestureModel
 24      */
 25     var _modelModule = null;
 26     /**
 27      * Gesture model module.
 28      * @type GeForMT.Parser
 29      * @default null
 30      */
 31     var _parserModule = null;
 32     /**
 33      * Visual feedback module.
 34      * @type GeForMT.VisualFeedback
 35      * @default null
 36      */
 37     var _feedbackModule = null;
 38     /**
 39      * Default generated parser component PEG.GeneratedGeForMTParser.
 40      * @type Object Contains a method that ist refereing to concrete parser implementation.
 41      */
 42     var _defaultParser = {
 43         identifier: 'PEGParser',
 44         adapter: function(expr){
 45             return PEG.GeneratedGeForMTParser.parse(expr);
 46         }
 47     };
 48     /**
 49      * Default selector engine component Sizzle.
 50      * @type Object Contains method that is refering to Sizzle.
 51      *
 52      */
 53     var _defaultEngine = {
 54             identifier: 'Sizzle',
 55             adapter: function(selector){
 56                 return Sizzle(selector, document);
 57             }
 58     };
 59     /**
 60      * TemplateBuilder module.
 61      * @type GeForMT.TemplateBuilding
 62      * @default null
 63      */
 64     var _templateBuilder = null;
 65     
 66     /**
 67      * Recognition module.
 68      * @type GeForMT.GestureRecognition
 69      * @default null
 70      */
 71     var _recognitionModule = null;
 72     /**
 73      * Selector Engine module.
 74      * @type GeForMT.SelectorEngine
 75      * @default null
 76      */
 77     var _selectorEngineModule = null;
 78     /**
 79      * Observation module.
 80      * @type GeForMT.Observation
 81      * @default null
 82      */
 83     var _observationModule = null;
 84     
 85     /**
 86      * Components already initialized?
 87      * @type Boolean
 88      * @default false
 89      */
 90     var _componentsInitialized = false;
 91     /**
 92      * Default settings.
 93      * @type Object
 94      * @private
 95      */
 96     var _defaultSettings = {
 97         /**
 98          * Setting to prevent the browser's default behaviour while catching user input events.
 99          * @type Boolean
100          * @default true
101          */
102         preventDefault: true,
103         /**
104          * Setting to enable or disable visual feedback while drawing a gesture.
105          * @type Boolean
106          * @default true
107          */
108         feedback: true,
109         /**
110          * Contiguity interval in milliseconds. Time listening on subsequent compound interaction
111          * after a performed gesture.
112          */
113         contiguityInterval: 1000
114     
115     };
116     
117     /**
118      * Custom settings.
119      * @private
120      * @default null
121      * @type Object
122      */
123     var _customSettings = null;
124     
125     /**
126      * Custom gestures.
127      * @private
128      * @default null
129      * @type Object
130      */
131     var _customGestures = null;
132     
133     /**
134      * Initialize modules and classes for gesture recognition.
135      * @private
136      */
137     function _initComponents(){
138     
139         // Initialize parser component
140         _parserModule = GeForMT.Parser;
141         _parserModule.registerParser(_defaultParser.identifier, _defaultParser.adapter);
142         _parserModule.init(_defaultParser.identifier);
143         
144         // Initialize gesture model module
145         _modelModule = GeForMT.GestureModel;
146         _modelModule.init();
147         
148         // Initialize Selector Engine
149         _selectorEngineModule = GeForMT.SelectorEngine;
150         var defaultSelectorEngine = _defaultEngine;
151             _selectorEngineModule.registerEngine(defaultSelectorEngine.identifier, defaultSelectorEngine.adapter);
152             _selectorEngineModule.init(defaultSelectorEngine.identifier);
153         
154         //Initialize observation module
155         _observationModule = GeForMT.Observation;
156         
157         var preventDefault = _defaultSettings.preventDefault;
158         if (typeof _customSettings != 'undefined') {
159             if (typeof _customSettings.preventDefault != 'undefined') {
160                 preventDefault = _customSettings.preventDefault;
161             }
162         }
163         _observationModule.init(preventDefault);
164         
165         // Initialize template builder component
166         _templateBuilder = GeForMT.TemplateBuilder;
167         _templateBuilder.init();
168         
169         
170         // Initialize gesture recognizer
171         _recognitionModule = GeForMT.GestureRecognition;
172         var contiguity = _defaultSettings.contiguityInterval;
173         if (typeof _customSettings != 'undefined') {
174             if (typeof _customSettings.contiguityInterval != 'undefined') {
175                 contiguity = _customSettings.contiguityInterval;
176             }
177         }
178         _recognitionModule.init(_modelModule, _observationModule, _templateBuilder, contiguity);
179         _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener('gesturerecognized', _gestureRecognized);
180         
181         // Initialize visual feedback
182         _feedbackModule = GeForMT.VisualFeedback;
183         _feedbackModule.init(_observationModule, _recognitionModule);
184         if (typeof _customSettings != 'undefined') {
185             if (typeof _customSettings.feedback != 'undefined') {
186             
187                 _feedbackModule.setVisualFeedback(_customSettings.feedback);
188             }
189             else {
190             
191                 _feedbackModule.setVisualFeedback(_defaultSettings.feedback);
192             }
193         }
194         
195     }
196     
197     /**
198      * Initialize a set of custom gestures.
199      * @private
200      */
201     function _initGestures(){
202         var gestureSets = [];
203         
204         //add custom gestures
205         if (typeof _customGestures != 'undefined') {
206             gestureSets.push(_customGestures);
207         }
208         for (var i in gestureSets) {
209             var gestureSet = gestureSets[i];
210             for (var key in gestureSet) {
211                 var gestureConfig = gestureSet[key];
212                 // overwrite identifier with key if not defined
213                 if (typeof gestureConfig.identifier == 'undefined') {
214                     gestureConfig.identifier = key;
215                 }
216                 var gesture=_checkExpressionForReusedIdentifier(gestureConfig);
217                 gesture = _initSingleGesture(gesture);
218                 _addToGestureModel(gesture);
219             }
220             
221         }
222         
223   }
224     
225     /**
226      * Initialize a single gesture.
227      * @param {String} name  The identifier of the gesture. Must be unique.
228      * @param {String} expression  Formal expression according to GeForMT grammar.
229      * @param {Function} eventhandler Callback function as gesture event listener.
230      * @private
231      */
232     function _initSingleGesture(config){
233         // temporary gesture object
234         var GestureConfig = config;
235         // raw model from parser
236         GestureConfig.rawModel = null;
237         // adapted model
238         GestureConfig.model = null;
239         
240         var identifier = config.identifier;
241         
242         // parse GeForMT expression and get a raw model from generated parser
243         try {
244             GestureConfig.rawModel = _parserModule.parse(GestureConfig.expr);
245         } 
246         catch (e) {
247             // throw own exception with additional information
248             throw "Exception while parsing the expression [" +
249             GestureConfig.expr +
250             "] of gesture with identifier [" +
251             identifier +
252             "]: \n " +
253             e;
254         }
255         
256         // create an adapted gesture object model from raw model of the parser
257         GestureConfig.model = _modelModule.createGestureObjectModel();
258         var options = GestureConfig.rawModel.options;
259         
260         
261         for (var i = 0; i < options.length; i++) {
262             var rawComplex = options[i];
263             // var complexGesture=null;
264             // console.debug(complexGesture);
265             var complexGesture = _modelModule.createComplexGesture(rawComplex.relation);
266             
267             GestureConfig.model.addOption(complexGesture);
268             
269             var multistrokeGesture = false;
270             var synchronousMultitouchGesture = false;
271             var asynchronousMultitouchGesture = false;
272             
273             // iterate through list of composed gestures first time to find out the type of composition and summerize	
274             for (var m = 0; m < rawComplex.gestures.length; m++) {
275                 var gst_current = rawComplex.gestures[m + 1];
276                 var gst_next = rawComplex.gestures[m + 1];
277                 
278                 //check whether a second gesture exists, that is connected with a COMMA operation and has the same function
279                 if (typeof gst_next !== 'undefined') {
280                 
281                     switch (gst_next.operation) {
282                         case GeForMT.OPERATION_TYPES.COMMA:
283                             if (gst_current.funct.number == gst_next.funct.number &&
284                             gst_current.funct.type == gst_next.funct.type) {
285                                 // in this part all gestures that are connected with COMMA will be
286                                 // summerized
287                                 
288                                 
289                                 //add content of next gesture to current gesture path to create a continous gesture path
290                                 rawComplex.gestures[m].atomfocus = rawComplex.gestures[m].atomfocus.concat(rawComplex.gestures[m + 1].atomfocus);
291                                 // delete next gesture
292                                 rawComplex.gestures.splice(m + 1, 1);
293                             }
294                             else {
295                             // this will be not supported in this version!!!
296                             //TODO: Exception
297                             }
298                             break;
299                         case GeForMT.OPERATION_TYPES.SEMICOLON:
300                             if (synchronousMultitouchGesture || asynchronousMultitouchGesture) {
301                             //TODO: mixed composition not supported!
302                             // Exception.
303                             }
304                             else {
305                                 multistrokeGesture = true;
306                                 complexGesture.isMultistrokeGesture = multistrokeGesture;
307                                 
308                             }
309                             break;
310                         case GeForMT.OPERATION_TYPES.ASTERISK:
311                             if (multistrokeGesture) {
312                             //TODO: mixed composition not supported in this version!
313                             // Exception.
314                             }
315                             else {
316                                 synchronousMultitouchGesture = true;
317                                 complexGesture.isSynchronousComposedGesture = synchronousMultitouchGesture;
318                             //???
319                             }
320                             break;
321                         case GeForMT.OPERATION_TYPES.PLUS:
322                             if (multistrokeGesture) {
323                             //TODO: mixed composition not supported in this version!
324                             // Exception.
325                             }
326                             else {
327                                 asynchronousMultitouchGesture = true;
328                                 complexGesture.isAsynchronousComposedGesture = synchronousMultitouchGesture;
329                                 
330                             //???
331                             }
332                             break;
333                     }
334                     
335                 }
336                 else {
337                     //only one gesture exist in the definition
338                     // TODO: set info in model
339                 }
340             }
341             
342             //iterate through adapted list of composed gestures
343             for (var gestureKey = 0; gestureKey < rawComplex.gestures.length; gestureKey++) {
344                 var rawGesture = rawComplex.gestures[gestureKey];
345                 
346                 // create atomic gesture
347                 var functNum = rawGesture.funct !== null ? rawGesture.funct.number : null;
348                 var functType = rawGesture.funct !== null ? rawGesture.funct.type : null;
349                 var rawGestureSequence = rawGesture.atomfocus;
350                 
351                 var rotationInvariant = true;
352                 
353                 var tmpGestureTemplates = null;
354                 var numOfGesturesInGestureSequenceTemplate = 0;
355                 var tmpFocuslist = [];
356                 
357                 for (var j = 0; j < rawGestureSequence.length; j++) {
358                 
359                     //get gesture type and create type objects
360                     var rawAtomType = rawGestureSequence[j].atom;
361                     var atomicGestureType = rawAtomType.type;
362                     
363                     var additionalFocuslist = rawGestureSequence[j].focuslist;
364                     
365                     if (atomicGestureType === GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.POINT ||
366                     atomicGestureType === GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.HOLD ||
367                     atomicGestureType === GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.DEPOINT ||
368                     atomicGestureType === GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.MOVE) {
369                         // case if a POINT,HOLD, DEPOINT or MOVE gesture was found in the gesture sequence
370                         var elementPartList = null;
371                         var atomicPartGesture = null;
372                         
373                         
374                         //save last gesture sequence						
375                         if (tmpGestureTemplates !== null) {
376                             // get elements by selector engine
377                             elementPartList = tmpFocuslist.length !== 0 ? _selectorEngineModule.getElements(tmpFocuslist) : null;
378                             
379                             if (numOfGesturesInGestureSequenceTemplate > 1) {
380                                 atomicGestureType = GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.COMPLEX_SHAPE;
381                                 rotationInvariant = true;
382                             }
383                             else {
384                                 rotationInvariant = typeof rawAtomType.direction == 'undefined' ? false : true;
385                             }
386                             
387                             // create and register atomic gesture
388                             atomicPartGesture = _modelModule.createAtomicGesture(atomicGestureType, elementPartList, functType, functNum, tmpGestureTemplates, rotationInvariant);
389                             complexGesture.composite.push(atomicPartGesture);
390                             
391                             // register observation of Node objects that belong
392                             // to the gesture
393                             _observationModule.addEventObservation(identifier, atomicPartGesture.elementList);
394                             
395                         }
396                         
397                         // get elements by selector engine
398                         elementPartList = additionalFocuslist !== null ? _selectorEngineModule.getElements(additionalFocuslist) : null;
399                         
400                         // create and register atomic gesture like POINT, HOLD, DEPOINT or MOVE
401                         atomicPartGesture = _modelModule.createAtomicGesture(atomicGestureType, elementPartList, functType, functNum, null, null);
402                         complexGesture.composite.push(atomicPartGesture);
403                         
404                         // register observation of Node objects that belong to
405                         // the gesture
406                         _observationModule.addEventObservation(identifier, atomicPartGesture.elementList);
407                         
408                         tmpGestureTemplates = null;
409                         numOfGesturesInGestureSequenceTemplate = 0;
410                         tmpFocuslist = [];
411                     }
412                     else {
413                         // case if an atomic path gesture was found 
414                         // create template representing the gesture path
415                         
416                         if (rawGestureSequence.length == 1) {
417                             //if only one atom of a gesture exist in the gesture sequence
418                             //then the strategy of rotation invariance can be used
419                             rotationInvariant = false;
420                         }
421                         else {
422                             rotationInvariant = true;
423                         }
424                         
425                         
426                         tmpGestureTemplates = _templateBuilder.createListOfTemplatesBasedOnFormalization(atomicGestureType, rawAtomType.direction, rawAtomType.rotation, tmpGestureTemplates, rotationInvariant);
427                         
428                         numOfGesturesInGestureSequenceTemplate++;
429                         tmpFocuslist = tmpFocuslist.concat(additionalFocuslist);
430                     }
431                     
432                 }
433                 
434                 //create an atomic gesture
435                 if (tmpGestureTemplates !== null) {
436                     // get elements by selector engine
437                     var elementList = tmpFocuslist.length !== 0 ? _selectorEngineModule.getElements(tmpFocuslist) : null;
438                     
439                     if (numOfGesturesInGestureSequenceTemplate > 1) {
440                         atomicGestureType = GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.COMPLEX_SHAPE;
441                         rotationInvariant = true;
442                     }
443                     else {
444                         rotationInvariant = typeof rawAtomType.direction == 'undefined' ? false : true;
445                     }
446                     
447                     
448                     //create and register atomic gesture
449                     var atomicGesture = _modelModule.createAtomicGesture(atomicGestureType, elementList, functType, functNum, tmpGestureTemplates, rotationInvariant);
450                     complexGesture.composite.push(atomicGesture);
451                     
452                     
453                     
454                     // register observation of Node objects that belong to the
455                     // gesture
456                     _observationModule.addEventObservation(identifier, atomicGesture.elementList);
457                     
458                 }
459                 
460             }
461             
462             
463         }       
464         //console.debug(GestureConfig);
465         //console.debug("ID: "+identifier+", GeForMT: "+GestureConfig.expr+", Template: "+tmpGestureTemplate.points.length);
466         
467         
468         // addtemplate
469         // _recognitionModule.registerTemplate(gestureSet[key].identifier,
470         // template);
471         
472         // register complete gesture object in gesture model module
473         return GestureConfig;
474     }
475     /**
476      * Replace all reused gesture identifier in GeForMT expressions.
477      * Reused identifiers in an expression must start and end with symbols '<' and '>'.
478      * Example gesture definition: LINE_N;<gestureIdentifier>;LINE_N. Only gestures that already have been registered can be used.
479      * @param {Object} gestureConfig
480      */
481     function _checkExpressionForReusedIdentifier(gestureConfig){
482         var gestureId = gestureConfig.identifier;
483         var gestureExpr = gestureConfig.expr;
484         var registeredGestures = _modelModule.getAllGestures();
485         
486         for (var i = 0; i < registeredGestures.length; i++) {
487 			var regex=new RegExp("<"+registeredGestures[i].identifier+">","g");
488 			var repl=registeredGestures[i].expr;
489         	gestureExpr=gestureExpr.replace(regex, repl);
490         }
491 		gestureConfig.expr=gestureExpr;
492 		return gestureConfig;
493     }
494     
495     /**
496      * Add a single gesture to gesture model.
497      * @param {Object} gesture A single custom gesture.
498      * @return {Boolean}
499      * @private
500      */
501     function _addToGestureModel(gesture){
502         var success = (_modelModule !== null) ? _modelModule.addGesture(gesture) : false;
503         return success;
504     }
505     
506     /**
507      * Event handler receiving events if a gesture has been recognized
508      * @param {GeForMT.GestureRecognition.GestureRecognizedEvent} e
509      */
510     function _gestureRecognized(e){
511         var gesture = _modelModule.getGestureById(e.identifier);
512         gesture.handler(e);
513     }
514     /**
515      * Helper class to setup the object structure for the gesture that has to be registered.
516      * @class
517      * @param {String} id
518      * @param {String} expression
519      * @param {Function} eventhandler
520      * @param {Boolean} on 
521      * @param {String} descr
522      */
523     function GestureConfig(id, expression, eventhandler, on, descr){
524         return {
525             identifier: id,
526             expr: expression,
527             handler: eventhandler,
528             online: on,
529             description: descr
530         };
531     }
532     
533     return {
534     
535         /**
536          * Initialize framework components.
537          * @param {Object} customSettings Custom defined settings.
538          * @param {Object} customGestures Custom defined gestures.
539          * @public
540          */
541         init: function(customGestures, customSettings){
542         	 if (!_componentsInitialized) {
543             _customSettings = customSettings;
544             _customGestures = customGestures;
545             
546             _initComponents();
547             _initGestures();
548             _componentsInitialized = true;
549         	 }
550         },
551         
552         /**
553          * Initialize gesture.
554          * @param  {GeForMT.GestureConfig} gestureConfig Object literal that contains gesture definition parameters.
555          */
556         addGesture: function(gestureConfig){
557             if (!_componentsInitialized) {
558                 //Warning/ Exception
559             }
560             else {
561                var gesture= _checkExpressionForReusedIdentifier(gestureConfig);
562                gesture = _initSingleGesture(gesture);
563                 _addToGestureModel(gesture);
564             }
565             
566         },
567          /**
568          * Remove a gesture.
569          * @param  {String} identifier Identifier of the gesture
570          */
571         removeGesture: function(identifier){
572             if (!_componentsInitialized) {
573                 //Warning/ Exception
574             }
575             else {
576                _observationModule.removeGestureFromEventObservation(identifier);
577                _modelModule.removeGesture(identifier);
578             }
579             
580         },
581         /**
582          * Register for an atomic GestureEvent, representing a generelized event for mouse and touch interaction,
583          * dispatched by the GeForMT.Observation module.
584          * @param  {String} name The type name of the event. Must be gesturestart, gesturemove or gestureend.
585          * @param  {Function} eventhandler Callback function as gesture event listener.
586          */
587         addGestureEventListener: function(type, eventhandler){
588             if (_observationModule !== null &&
589             typeof _observationModule != "undefined") {
590                 _observationModule.registerGestureEventListener(type, eventhandler);
591             }
592         },
593         /**
594          * Register for 'recognitionfailed'-Event of gesture recognition module.
595          * @param {Function} eventhandler Callback function.
596          */
597         addRecognitionFailedEventListener: function(eventhandler){
598             if (_recognitionModule !== null &&
599             typeof _recognitionModule != "undefined") {
600                 _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener("recognitionfailed", eventhandler);
601             }
602         },
603         /**
604          * Register for 'recognitionstarted'-Event of gesture recognition module.
605          * @param {Function} eventhandler Callback function.
606          */
607         addRecognitionStartedEventListener: function(eventhandler){
608             if (_recognitionModule !== null &&
609             typeof _recognitionModule != "undefined") {
610                 _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener("recognitionstarted", eventhandler);
611             }
612         },
613         /**
614          * Register for 'candidatesrecognized'-Event of gesture recognition module.
615          * @param {Function} eventhandler Callback function.
616          */
617         addRecognizedCandidatesEventListener: function(eventhandler){
618             if (_recognitionModule !== null &&
619             typeof _recognitionModule != "undefined") {
620                 _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener("candidatesrecognized", eventhandler);
621             }
622         },
623         /**
624          * Constructor of gesture configuration refering to GeForMT.GestureConfig.
625          * @class
626          * @param {String} id Identifier of the gesture. (Must be unique!) (required)
627          * @param {Object} expression Formal GeForMT expression. (required)
628          * @param {Function} eventhandler Event handler that will be notified, if the gesture has been recognized. (required)
629          * @param {Boolean} on Online or Offline recognition. (optional)
630          * @param {String} descr Description of the gesture. (optional)
631          */
632         Gesture: GestureConfig
633     
634     };
635 })();
636 /**
637  * Enumeration of constant operation types.
638  * @namespace
639  */
640 GeForMT.OPERATION_TYPES = /*@lends*/{
641     /**
642      * Operation type for asynchronous composition gestures.
643      * @constant
644      */
645     PLUS: 0,
646     /**
647      * Operation type for synchronous composition gestures.
648      * @constant
649      */
650     ASTERISK: 1,
651     /**
652      * Operation type for sequential composition of coherent gestures.
653      * @constant
654      */
655     COMMA: 2,
656     /**
657      * Operation type defining gestures as options.
658      * @constant
659      */
660     OPTION: 3,
661     /**
662      * Operation type for sequential composition of incoherent (that means the operation includes a DEPOINT gesture) gestures.
663      * @constant
664      */
665     SEMICOLON: 4
666 };
667 /**
668  * Enumeration of constant relation types.
669  * @namespace
670  */
671 GeForMT.RELATION_TYPES = /*@lends*/{
672     /**
673      * Relation type for crossing gestures.
674      * @constant
675      */
676     CROSS: 5,
677     /**
678      * Relation type for gestures that are moving towards each other.
679      * @constant
680      */
681     JOIN: 6,
682     /**
683      * Relation type parallel execution of gestures.
684      * @constant
685      */
686     SYNC: 7,
687     /**
688      * Relation type for gestures that are moving away from each other.
689      * @constant
690      */
691     SPLIT: 8,
692     /**
693      * Relation type for connected at start position of the gestures.
694      * @constant
695      */
696     CONNECT_START: 9,
697     /**
698      * Relation type for connected at end position of the gestures.
699      * @constant
700      */
701     CONNECT_END: 10,
702      /**
703      * Relation type for gestures performed among each other.
704      * @constant
705      */
706      AMONG: 11,
707   /**
708      * Relation type for gestures performed aside each other.
709      * @constant
710      */
711      ASIDE: 12,
712       /**
713      * Relation type for closed gesture pathes.
714      * @constant
715      */
716      CLOSE: 13
717 };
718 /**
719  * Enumeration of constant identifier types.
720  * @namespace
721  */
722 GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES = /*@lends*/{
723 	/**
724 	 * Represents an unspecified movement.
725 	 * @constant
726 	 */
727     MOVE: 10,
728     /**
729 	 * Represents a pointing gesture.
730 	 * @constant
731 	 */
732     POINT: 11,
733      /**
734 	 * Holding the finger on a position.
735 	 * @constant
736 	 */
737     HOLD: 12,
738    /**
739 	 * Represents lifting the finger.
740 	 * @constant
741 	 */
742     DEPOINT: 13
743 };
744 /**
745  * Enumeration of constant shape types.
746  * @namespace
747  */
748 GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES = /*@lends*/{
749 	  /**
750 	 * Represents a circular movement.
751 	 * @constant
752 	 */
753     CIRCLE: 14,
754     /**
755 	 * Represents a half circle.
756 	 * @constant
757 	 */
758     SEMICIRCLE: 15,
759      /**
760 	 * Represents a composed (connected, that means composition with KOMMA operation) gesture.
761 	 * @constant
762 	 */

917 			}
918 		},
919

936 				//Warning: Parser with this identifier exists and will be overwritten
937 			}
938 			Parser[name] = parseFunction;
939 		 }

3433       function parse_integer() {
3434         var cacheKey = 'integer@' + pos;
3435         var cachedResult = cache[cacheKey];
3436         if (cachedResult) {
3437           pos = cachedResult.nextPos;
3438           return cachedResult.result;
3439         }
3440         
3441         
3442         var savedPos0 = pos;
3443         var savedPos1 = pos;
3444         if (input.substr(pos).match(/^[1-9]/) !== null) {
3445           var result3 = input.charAt(pos);
3446           pos++;
3447         } else {
3448           var result3 = null;
3449           if (reportMatchFailures) {
3450             matchFailed("[1-9]");
3451           }
3452         }
3453         if (result3 !== null) {
3454           var result4 = [];
3455           if (input.substr(pos).match(/^[0-9]/) !== null) {
3456             var result5 = input.charAt(pos);
3457             pos++;
3458           } else {
3459             var result5 = null;
3460             if (reportMatchFailures) {
3461               matchFailed("[0-9]");
3462             }
3463           }
3464           while (result5 !== null) {
3465             result4.push(result5);
3466             if (input.substr(pos).match(/^[0-9]/) !== null) {
3467               var result5 = input.charAt(pos);
3468               pos++;
3469             } else {
3470               var result5 = null;
3471               if (reportMatchFailures) {
3472                 matchFailed("[0-9]");
3473               }
3474             }
3475           }
3476           if (result4 !== null) {
3477             var result1 = [result3, result4];
3478           } else {
3479             var result1 = null;
3480             pos = savedPos1;
3481           }
3482         } else {
3483           var result1 = null;
3484           pos = savedPos1;
3485         }
3486         var result2 = result1 !== null
3487           ? (function(first_digit, last_digits) {	var digits=String(first_digit)+String(last_digits.join(""));
3488           			return parseInt(digits,10);
3489           		})(result1[0], result1[1])
3490           : null;
3491         if (result2 !== null) {
3492           var result0 = result2;
3493         } else {
3494           var result0 = null;
3495           pos = savedPos0;
3496         }
3497         
3498         
3499         
3500         cache[cacheKey] = {
3501           nextPos: pos,
3502           result:  result0
3503         };
3504         return result0;
3505       }
3506       
3507       function buildErrorMessage() {
3508         function buildExpected(failuresExpected) {
3509           failuresExpected.sort();
3510           
3511           var lastFailure = null;
3512           var failuresExpectedUnique = [];
3513           for (var i = 0; i < failuresExpected.length; i++) {
3514             if (failuresExpected[i] !== lastFailure) {
3515               failuresExpectedUnique.push(failuresExpected[i]);
3516               lastFailure = failuresExpected[i];
3517             }
3518           }
3519           
3520           switch (failuresExpectedUnique.length) {
3521             case 0:
3522               return 'end of input';
3523             case 1:
3524               return failuresExpectedUnique[0];
3525             default:
3526               return failuresExpectedUnique.slice(0, failuresExpectedUnique.length - 1).join(', ')
3527                 + ' or '
3528                 + failuresExpectedUnique[failuresExpectedUnique.length - 1];
3529           }
3530         }
3531         
3532         var expected = buildExpected(rightmostMatchFailuresExpected);
3533         var actualPos = Math.max(pos, rightmostMatchFailuresPos);
3534         var actual = actualPos < input.length
3535           ? quote(input.charAt(actualPos))
3536           : 'end of input';
3537         
3538         return 'Expected ' + expected + ' but ' + actual + ' found.';
3539       }
3540       
3541       function computeErrorPosition() {
3542         /*
3543          * The first idea was to use |String.split| to break the input up to the
3544          * error position along newlines and derive the line and column from
3545          * there. However IE's |split| implementation is so broken that it was
3546          * enough to prevent it.
3547          */
3548         
3549         var line = 1;
3550         var column = 1;
3551         var seenCR = false;
3552         
3553         for (var i = 0; i <  rightmostMatchFailuresPos; i++) {
3554           var ch = input.charAt(i);
3555           if (ch === '\n') {
3556             if (!seenCR) { line++; }
3557             column = 1;
3558             seenCR = false;
3559           } else if (ch === '\r' | ch === '\u2028' || ch === '\u2029') {
3560             line++;
3561             column = 1;
3562             seenCR = true;
3563           } else {
3564             column++;
3565             seenCR = false;
3566           }
3567         }
3568         
3569         return { line: line, column: column };
3570       }
3571       
3572       
3573       
3574       var result = parseFunctions[startRule]();
3575       
3576       /*
3577        * The parser is now in one of the following three states:
3578        *
3579        * 1. The parser successfully parsed the whole input.
3580        *
3581        *    - |result !== null|
3582        *    - |pos === input.length|
3583        *    - |rightmostMatchFailuresExpected| may or may not contain something
3584        *
3585        * 2. The parser successfully parsed only a part of the input.
3586        *
3587        *    - |result !== null|
3588        *    - |pos < input.length|
3589        *    - |rightmostMatchFailuresExpected| may or may not contain something
3590        *
3591        * 3. The parser did not successfully parse any part of the input.
3592        *
3593        *   - |result === null|
3594        *   - |pos === 0|
3595        *   - |rightmostMatchFailuresExpected| contains at least one failure
3596        *
3597        * All code following this comment (including called functions) must
3598        * handle these states.
3599        */
3600       if (result === null || pos !== input.length) {
3601         var errorPosition = computeErrorPosition();
3602         throw new this.SyntaxError(
3603           buildErrorMessage(),
3604           errorPosition.line,
3605           errorPosition.column
3606         );
3607       }
3608       
3609       return result;
3610     },
3611     
3612     /* Returns the parser source code. */
3613     toSource: function() { return this._source; }
3614   };
3615   
3616   /* Thrown when a parser encounters a syntax error. */
3617   
3618   result.SyntaxError = function(message, line, column) {
3619     this.name = 'SyntaxError';
3620     this.message = message;
3621     this.line = line;
3622     this.column = column;
3623   };
3624   
3625   result.SyntaxError.prototype = Error.prototype;
3626   
3627   return result;

3793     function AtomicGesture(gestureType, elementList, functionType, numberOfContacts,templates,rotationInvariant){
3794         if (typeof numberOfContacts != this.numberOfContacts) {
3795             this.numberOfContacts = numberOfContacts;
3796         }
3797         if (functionType != this.functionType && functionType !== null) {
3798             this.functionType = functionType;
3799         }
3800         if (this.numberOfContacts != numberOfContacts && numberOfContacts !== null) {
3801             this.numberOfContacts = numberOfContacts;
3802         }
3803         if (gestureType != this.gestureType) {
3804             this.gestureType = gestureType;
3805         }
3806         
3807         if (typeof elementList != 'undefined' && elementList !== null && elementList.length !== 0) {
3808             this.elementList = elementList;
3809         }
3810 
3811 		if (typeof templates != 'undefined' && templates !== null) {
3812             this.templates = templates;
3813 			this.isPathGesture=true;
3814         }
3815 
3816 		if (typeof rotationInvariant != 'undefined' && rotationInvariant !== null && rotationInvariant !== this.rotationInvariant) {
3817             this.rotationInvariant = rotationInvariant;
3818         }

3881          */

3883

3885         
3886         /**
3887          * Adds a single gesture to data model.
3888          * @type Gesture
3889          * @param  {Object} gestureConfig Gesture configuration as object literal.
3890          * @return {GeForMT.GestureModel.Gesture} Returns the registered gesture. Returns null if registration and model creating failes.
3891          * @public
3892          */
3893         addGesture: function(gestureConfig){
3894         	var object=gestureConfig;
3895             if (typeof object != 'undefined') {
3896                 var gesture = new Gesture();
3897                 
3898                 // check object variables and copy to internal gesture object
3899                 if (object.identifier!==null && object.identifier !=="" && typeof object.identifier !== 'undefined') {
3900                     gesture.identifier = object.identifier;
3901                 }
3902                 else {
3903 					throw  "Exception while initializing the gesture with identifier [" + object.identifier
3904 					+ "]: \n Identifier is '', null or undefined!";
3905                     //console.debug("No Identifier!");
3906                 }
3907                 if (object.expr !==null && object.expr !=="" && typeof object.expr !== 'undefined') {
3908                     gesture.expr = object.expr;
3909                 }
3910                 else {
3911 					throw  "Exception while initializing the gesture with identifier [" + object.identifier
3912 					+ "]: \n No expression that defines the gesture!";
3913                     //console.debug("No expression that defines the gesture!");
3914                 }
3915                 if (object.handler !==null && object.handler !== "" && typeof object.handler !== 'undefined') {
3916                     gesture.handler = object.handler;
3917                 }
3918                 else {
3919 					throw  "Exception while initializing the gesture with identifier [" + object.identifier
3920 					+ "]: \n No event handler defined for this gesture!";
3921                     //console.debug("No Event Handler!");
3922                 }
3923                 if (typeof object.description !== 'undefined') {
3924                     gesture.description = object.description;
3925                 }
3926                 if (typeof object.model !== 'undefined') {
3927                     gesture.model = object.model;
3928                 }
3929                 else {
3930                     console.debug("Object model not defined!");
3931                     return null;
3932                 }
3933                 if (typeof object.online !== 'undefined') {
3934                     gesture.online = object.online;
3935                 }
3936                 
3937                 // add gesture to list
3938                 _gestures.push(gesture);
3939                 
3940                 return gesture;
3941                 
3942             }
3943             else {
3944                 return null;
3945             }
3946             
3947         },
3948         /**
3949          * Remove gesture from gesture model.
3950          * @param {String} identifier Unique identifier of the gesture that has to be removed.
3951          */
3952         removeGesture: function(identifier){
3953         	for (var key in _gestures) {
3954                 if (_gestures[key].identifier == identifier) {
3955                     _gestures.splice(key,1);
3956                     break;
3957                 }
3958             }
3959         },
3960         
3961         /**
3962          * Get gesture by identifier.
3963          * @param identifier {String} Identifier of the gesture.
3964          * @public
3965          * @return {GeForMT.GestureModel.Gesture} Returns object Gesture. Return null, if no gesture with the given identifier was found.
3966          */
3967         getGestureById: function(identifier){
3968             var gesture = null;
3969             for (var key in _gestures) {
3970                 if (_gestures[key].identifier == identifier) {
3971                     gesture = _gestures[key];
3972                     break;
3973                 }
3974             }
3975             return gesture;
3976         },
3977         
3978         /**
3979          * Get gestures by formal expression.
3980          * @param  {String} expr Identifier of the gesture.
3981          * @return {Array} Returns an array of Gesture objects. Return null, if no gesture with the given identifier was found.
3982          * @public
3983          */
3984         getGesturesByExpr: function(expr){
3985             var gestures = null;
3986             for (var key in _gestures) {
3987                 if (_gestures[key].expr == expr) {
3988                     gestures.push(_gestures[key]);
3989                     
3990                 }
3991             }
3992             return gesture;
3993         },
3994

4037 GeForMT.TemplateBuilder = ( function() {
4038 
4039 		/**
4040 		 * Number of points.
4041 		 * @type Number
4042 		 * @default 64
4043 		 */
4044 	var numberOfPoints= 64;
4045 		/**
4046 		 * Distance between points.
4047 		 * @type Number
4048 		 * @default 1
4049 		 */
4050  	var distanceOfPoints= 1;
4051 
4052 	/**
4053 	 * Constructor of a point, represented by x and y coordinate.
4054 	 * @class
4055 	 */
4056 	function Point(x, y) {
4057 		this.x = x;
4058 		this.y = y;
4059 	}
4060 
4061 	/**
4062 	 * Gesture template represented by facts like a point path, events, vector or sequence
4063 	 * of directions.
4064 	 * @class
4065 	 */
4066 	function Template(points) {
4067 		this.points = points;
4068 		this.events=[];
4069 		this.vectors=[]; 
4070 		//this.directions=[] // not implemented
4071 	}
4072 
4073 	Template.prototype = {
4074 		/**
4075 		 * Identifier of this template.
4076 		 */
4077 		 identifier: null,
4078 		/**
4079 		 * List of points representing a gesture.
4080 		 * @type Array
4081 		 * @default null
4082 		 */
4083 		points : null,
4084 		/**
4085 		 * List of events representing a gesture path. Used for candidate templates.
4086 		 * @type Array
4087 		 * @default null
4088 		 */
4089 		events : null,
4090 		/**
4091 		 * List of vectors representing a gesture.
4092 		 * @type Array
4093 		 * @default null
4094 		 */
4095 		vectors : null,
4096 		/**
4097 		 * List of directiontypes represented by constants in GeForMT.Types.DIRECTION_TYPES.
4098 		 * @type Array
4099 		 * @default null
4100 		 */
4101 		directions : null
4102 	};
4103 
4104 
4105 
4106 				/**
4107 		 * Get a list of template objects representing the path of a continous atomic gesture.
4108 		 * In contrast to method createTemplateFromGestureDefinition it generates templates 
4109 		 * even if direction or rotation are not defined. In this case a template for every direction and rotation will be created.
4110 		 * In case of concatenation of templates all variations are build. 
4111 		 * @param {GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES|GeForMT.VECTOR_TYPES|GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES} atomType The type of the atomic gesture.
4112 		 * @param {GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES} directionType The dirction type of the gesture.
4113 		 * @param {GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES} rotationType The rotation type of the gesture.
4114 		 * @param {Array} tmpTemplates List of template objects representing variations of the previous part of the gesture. The parts will be connected to a complex gesture path.
4115 		 */
4116 	function _createListOfTemplatesBasedOnFormalization(atomType,
4117 				directionType, rotationType, tmpTemplates,
4118 				useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
4119 			var templates = [];
4120 			switch (atomType) {
4121 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.POINT:
4122 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.HOLD:
4123 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.DEPOINT:
4124 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.MOVE:
4125 				templates = null;
4126 				break;
4127 			case GeForMT.VECTOR_TYPES.LINE:
4128 				if (typeof directionType !== 'undefined'
4129 						&& directionType !== null) {
4130 					templates.push(_createVectorTemplate(directionType));
4131 				} else {
4132 					templates
4133 							.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTH));
4134 					if (useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
4135 						templates
4136 								.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTH));
4137 						templates
4138 								.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.EAST));
4139 						templates
4140 								.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.WEST));
4141 						templates
4142 								.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTHWEST));
4143 						templates
4144 								.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTHEAST));
4145 						templates
4146 								.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTHWEST));
4147 						templates
4148 								.push(_createVectorTemplate(GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTHEAST));
4149 					}
4150 				}
4151 				break;
4152 			case GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.CIRCLE:
4153 			case GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.SEMICIRCLE:
4154 				if (typeof directionType !== 'undefined'
4155 						&& directionType !== null) {
4156 					if (typeof rotationType !== 'undefined'
4157 							&& rotationType !== null) {
4158 						templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4159 								directionType, rotationType));
4160 					} else {
4161 						templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType, directionType,
4162 										GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.CLOCKWISE));
4163 						templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4164 								directionType,
4165 								GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.COUNTERCLOCKWISE));
4166 					}
4167 				} else {
4168 					if (typeof rotationType !== 'undefined'
4169 							&& rotationType !== null) {
4170 						templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4171 								GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTH, rotationType));
4172 						if (useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
4173 
4174 							templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4175 											GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTH,
4176 											rotationType));
4177 							templates
4178 									.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4179 											GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.EAST,
4180 											rotationType));
4181 							templates
4182 									.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4183 											GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.WEST,
4184 											rotationType));
4185 						}
4186 					} else {
4187 						templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4188 								GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTH,
4189 								GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.CLOCKWISE));
4190 						templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4191 								GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTH,
4192 								GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.COUNTERCLOCKWISE));
4193 						if (useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
4194 
4195 							templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4196 									GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTH,
4197 									GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.CLOCKWISE));
4198 							templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4199 									GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTH,
4200 									GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.COUNTERCLOCKWISE));
4201 							templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4202 									GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.EAST,
4203 									GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.CLOCKWISE));
4204 							templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4205 									GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.EAST,
4206 									GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.COUNTERCLOCKWISE));
4207 							templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4208 									GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.WEST,
4209 									GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.CLOCKWISE));
4210 							templates.push(_createShapeTemplate(atomType,
4211 									GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.WEST,
4212 									GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.COUNTERCLOCKWISE));
4213 
4214 						}
4215 					}
4216 				}
4217 				break;
4218 
4219 			}
4220 
4221 			if (templates !== null && templates.length > 0
4222 					&& typeof tmpTemplates !== 'undefined'
4223 					&& tmpTemplates !== null) {
4224 				var newTemplates = [];
4225 				for ( var i = 0; i < tmpTemplates.length; i++) {
4226 					var prevTemplatePart = tmpTemplates[i];
4227 
4228 					for ( var j = 0; j < templates.length; j++) {
4229 						var concatTemplatePart = templates[j];
4230 						newTemplates.push(_concatTemplates(
4231 								prevTemplatePart, concatTemplatePart));
4232 					}
4233 
4234 				}
4235 
4236 				templates = newTemplates;
4237 			}
4238 			return templates;
4239 		}
4240 
4241 		/**
4242 		 * Get a template object representing the path of a continous atomic gesture.
4243 		 * @param {GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES|GeForMT.VECTOR_TYPES|GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES} atomType The type of the atomic gesture.
4244 		 * @param {GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES} directionType The dirction type of the gesture.
4245 		 * @param {GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES} rotationType The rotation type of the gesture.
4246 		 * @param {GeForMT.TemplateBuilding.Template} tmpTemplate List of Point objects representing the previous part of the gesture path. The parts will be connected to a complex gesture path.
4247 		 */
4248 		function _createTemplateBasedOnFormalization(atomType, directionType,
4249 				rotationType, tmpTemplate) {
4250 			var template = null;
4251 			switch (atomType) {
4252 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.POINT:
4253 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.HOLD:
4254 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.DEPOINT:
4255 			case GeForMT.CONTACT_TYPES.MOVE:
4256 				template = null;
4257 				break;
4258 			case GeForMT.VECTOR_TYPES.LINE:
4259 				template = _createVectorTemplate(directionType);
4260 				break;
4261 			case GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.CIRCLE:
4262 			case GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.SEMICIRCLE:
4263 				template = _createShapeTemplate(atomType, directionType,
4264 						rotationType);
4265 				break;
4266 
4267 			}
4268 
4269 			if (template !== null && typeof tmpTemplate !== 'undefined'
4270 					&& tmpTemplate !== null) {
4271 				template = _concatTemplates(tmpTemplate, template);
4272 			}
4273 			return template;
4274 		}
4275 		/**
4276 		 * Creates a list of points representing a vector.
4277 		 * @param {GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES} directionType
4278 		 * @return {Template} List of Point objects representing a vector.
4279 		 */
4280 		function _createVectorTemplate(directionType) {
4281 			var lineTemplate = [];
4282 
4283 			var refPoint = numberOfPoints * distanceOfPoints;
4284 
4285 			switch (directionType) {
4286 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTH:
4287 				for ( var i = 0; i < numberOfPoints
4288 						* distanceOfPoints; i += distanceOfPoints) {
4289 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint, refPoint - i));
4290 
4291 				}
4292 				break;
4293 
4294 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTH:
4295 				for ( var j = 0; j < numberOfPoints
4296 						* distanceOfPoints; j += distanceOfPoints) {
4297 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint, refPoint + j));
4298 
4299 				}
4300 				break;
4301 
4302 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.EAST:
4303 				for ( var k = 0; k < numberOfPoints
4304 						* distanceOfPoints; k += distanceOfPoints) {
4305 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint + k, refPoint));
4306 
4307 				}
4308 				break;
4309 
4310 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.WEST:
4311 				for ( var l = 0; l < numberOfPoints
4312 						* distanceOfPoints; l += distanceOfPoints) {
4313 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint - l, refPoint));
4314 
4315 				}
4316 				break;
4317 
4318 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTHEAST:
4319 				for ( var m = 0; m < numberOfPoints
4320 						* distanceOfPoints; m += distanceOfPoints) {
4321 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint + m, refPoint - m));
4322 
4323 				}
4324 				break;
4325 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTHWEST:
4326 				for ( var n = 0; n < numberOfPoints
4327 						* distanceOfPoints; n += distanceOfPoints) {
4328 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint - n, refPoint - n));
4329 				}
4330 				break;
4331 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTHEAST:
4332 				for ( var o = 0; o < numberOfPoints
4333 						* distanceOfPoints; o += distanceOfPoints) {
4334 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint + o, refPoint + o));
4335 				}
4336 				break;
4337 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTHWEST:
4338 				for ( var p = 0; p < numberOfPoints
4339 						* distanceOfPoints; p += distanceOfPoints) {
4340 					lineTemplate.push(new Point(refPoint - p, refPoint + p));
4341 
4342 				}
4343 				break;
4344 			}
4345 			return new Template(lineTemplate);
4346 		};
4347 
4348 		/**
4349 		 * Creates a list of points representing a circle or semicircle.
4350 		 * @param {GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES} shapeType
4351 		 * @param {GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES} directionType
4352 		 * @param {GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES} rotationType
4353 		 * @return {Template} List of Point objects representing a circle or semicircle.
4354 		 */
4355 		function _createShapeTemplate(shapeType, directionType, rotationType) {
4356 			var circleTemplate = [];
4357 
4358 			var r = (numberOfPoints * distanceOfPoints) / 2;
4359 
4360 			var refPoint = (numberOfPoints * distanceOfPoints) + 100;
4361 
4362 			var circleLength = 0;
4363 
4364 			var offset = 0;
4365 
4366 			switch (shapeType) {
4367 			case GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.CIRCLE:
4368 				circleLength = 2 * Math.PI;
4369 				circleOffset = Math.PI;
4370 				break;
4371 			case GeForMT.SHAPE_TYPES.SEMICIRCLE:
4372 				circleLength = Math.PI;
4373 				circleOffset = 0;
4374 				break;
4375 			}
4376 
4377 			switch (directionType) {
4378 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTH:
4379 				offset = 1 / 2 * Math.PI;
4380 				break;
4381 
4382 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTH:
4383 				offset = 3 / 2 * Math.PI;
4384 				break;
4385 
4386 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.EAST:
4387 				offset = Math.PI;
4388 				break;
4389 
4390 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.WEST:
4391 				offset = 0;// right
4392 				break;
4393 
4394 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTHEAST:
4395 				offset = 3 / 4 * Math.PI;
4396 				break;
4397 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.NORTHWEST:
4398 				offset = 1 / 4 * Math.PI;
4399 				break;
4400 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTHEAST:
4401 				offset = 5 / 4 * Math.PI;
4402 				break;
4403 			case GeForMT.DIRECTION_TYPES.SOUTHWEST:
4404 				offset = 7 / 4 * Math.PI;
4405 				break;
4406 			}
4407 
4408 			if (rotationType == GeForMT.ROTATION_TYPES.COUNTERCLOCKWISE) {
4409 				//rotation counterclockwise
4410 				for ( var a = 0 + offset; a < circleLength + offset; a = a
4411 						+ circleLength / numberOfPoints) {
4412 
4413 					var x = refPoint - r * Math.cos(a);
4414 					var y = refPoint - r * Math.sin(a);
4415 
4416 					circleTemplate.push(new Point(x, y));
4417 
4418 				}
4419 				circleTemplate.reverse();
4420 			} else {
4421 				for ( var a = 0 + offset + circleOffset; a < circleLength
4422 						+ offset + circleOffset; a = a + circleLength
4423 						/ numberOfPoints) {
4424 
4425 					//rotation clockwise
4426 					var x = refPoint + r * Math.cos(a);
4427 					var y = refPoint + r * Math.sin(a);
4428 
4429 					circleTemplate.push(new Point(x, y));
4430 				}
4431 			}
4432 			return new Template(circleTemplate);
4433 		};
4434 		/**
4435 		 * Concatenation of two templates (list of points that represent gesture pathes).
4436 		 * @param {Template} template1 A list of points that represents the first template.
4437 		 * @param {Template} template2 A list of points that represents the second template.
4438 		 * @return {Template} List of Point objects representing the path of a complex shape.
4439 		 */
4440 		function _concatTemplates(template1, template2) {
4441 			var lastPoint = template1.points[template1.points.length - 1];
4442 			var firstPoint = template2.points[0];
4443 
4444 			var diffX = Math.abs(lastPoint.x - firstPoint.x);
4445 			var diffY = Math.abs(lastPoint.y - firstPoint.y);
4446 
4447 			var offsetX = diffX;
4448 			var offsetY = diffY;
4449 			if (lastPoint.x <= firstPoint.x) {
4450 				offsetX = -offsetX;
4451 			}
4452 			if (lastPoint.y <= firstPoint.y) {
4453 				offsetY = -offsetY;
4454 			}
4455 
4456 			for ( var i = 0; i < template2.points.length; i++) {
4457 				template2.points[i].x = template2.points[i].x + offsetX;
4458 				template2.points[i].y = template2.points[i].y + offsetY;
4459 			}
4460 
4461 			var template = template1.points.concat(template2.points);
4462 
4463 			return new Template(template);
4464 		}
4465 		/**
4466 		 * Returns a list of templates representing all gesture pathes.
4467 		 * @param {Array} eventProfile List of events representing a performed gesture.
4468 		 * @return Array
4469 		 */
4470 		function _createTemplatesBasedOnEventProfile(eventProfile) {
4471 			var points = [];
4472 			var eventProfileLength = eventProfile.length;
4473 			var templates={};
4474 			var keys=[];
4475 			for ( var i = 0; i < eventProfileLength; i++) {
4476 				var contacts=eventProfile[i].contacts;
4477 				var contactsLength=contacts.length;
4478 				for(var j=0; j< contactsLength;j++){
4479 					var contact=contacts[j];
4480 					if(templates[contact.identifier]===null || typeof templates[contact.identifier] == 'undefined'){
4481 	        			//create gesture path with identifier as key
4482 	        			templates[contact.identifier]=new Template([]);
4483 	        			templates[contact.identifier].identifier=contact.identifier;
4484 	        			keys.push(contact.identifier);
4485 	        		}
4486 					
4487 					templates[contact.identifier].points.push(new Point(contact.pageX,contact.pageY));
4488 
4489 					templates[contact.identifier].events.push(eventProfile[i]);
4490 				}
4491 			}
4492 
4493 			var templateList=[];
4494 			for(var k=0;k<keys.length;k++){
4495 				//var normalizedTemplate = this.normalizeTemplate(templates[keys[k]],useBoundedRotationInvariance);
4496 				templateList.push(templates[keys[k]]);
4497 			}
4498 			
4499 			return templateList;
4500 		}
4501 		
4502 		/**
4503 		 * New events are transformed and integrated into existing templates with the intent to extend the template.
4504 		 * @param {Array} eventProfile List of new events.
4505 		 * @param {Array} templates Existing templates.
4506 		 */
4507 		function _updateTemplatesBasedOnEventProfile(eventProfile,templates) {
4508 			//build map with path identifier as key (helper)
4509 			var templatesMap = {};
4510 			var keys=[];
4511 			
4512 			for(var i=0;i<templates.length;i++){
4513 				templatesMap[templates[i].identifier]=templates[i];
4514 				keys.push(templates[i].identifier);
4515 			}
4516 			
4517 			//attach contact position
4518 			var eventProfileLength=eventProfile.length;
4519 			for ( var i = 0; i < eventProfileLength; i++) {
4520 				var contacts=eventProfile[i].contacts;
4521 				
4522 				for(var j=0; j< contacts.length;j++){
4523 					var contact=contacts[j];
4524 					//console.debug(templatesMap[contact.identifier]===null || typeof templatesMap[contact.identifier] == 'undefined');
4525 					if(templatesMap[contact.identifier]===null || typeof templatesMap[contact.identifier] == 'undefined'){
4526 	        			//create gesture path with identifier as key
4527 	        			templatesMap[contact.identifier]=new Template([]);
4528 	        			templatesMap[contact.identifier].identifier=contact.identifier;
4529 	        			keys.push(contact.identifier);
4530 	        			
4531 	        			
4532 	        		}
4533 					templatesMap[contact.identifier].points.push(new Point(contact.pageX,contact.pageY));
4534 
4535 					templatesMap[contact.identifier].events.push(eventProfile[i]);
4536 				}
4537 			}
4538 
4539 			var templateList=[];
4540 			for(var k=0;k<keys.length;k++){
4541 				//var normalizedTemplate = this.normalizeTemplate(templates[keys[k]],useBoundedRotationInvariance);
4542 				templateList.push(templatesMap[keys[k]]);
4543 			}
4544 			return templateList;
4545 		}

4601 GeForMT.SelectorEngine = (function(){
4602     /**
4603      * Enumeration of possible selector engines.
4604      * @type Object
4605      */
4606     var Engines = {};
4607     
4608     /**
4609      * Initialized selector engine.
4610      * @type Function
4611      * @default null
4612      * @private
4613      */
4614     var _engine = null;
4615     
4616     
4617     return {  
4618         /**
4619          * Initialize the selector engine by identifier. The engine ust be registered before it can be initialized.
4620          * @param {String} identifier Identifier of a registered selector engine.
4621          */
4622         init: function(identifier){
4623             _engine = Engines[identifier];
4624             //info of version and selector engine
4625         },
4626         /**
4627          * Get Element objects by a single selector expression or a list of selector expressions. A Selector Engine must be registered and initialized before it can be used.
4628          * @param  {String|Array} selector|list Single selector expression or a list of selector expressions.
4629          * @return {Array} A Node object or an array of Node objects.
4630          */
4631         getElements: function(selector){
4632             var nodeList = [];
4633 			
4634 			var elements=null;
4635             
4636             if (Array.isArray(selector)) {
4637 				for (var i = 0; i < selector.length; i++) {
4638 					elements = _engine(selector);
4639 					if(selector.length!==0 && selector!==null && elements.length==0){
4640             // throw exception
4641             throw "Exception while parsing the selector [" + selector + "]";
4642 					}
4643         	
4644 					if (Array.isArray(elements)) {
4645 						nodeList = nodeList.concat(elements);
4646 					}
4647 					else {
4648 						nodeList.push(elements);
4649 					}
4650 				}
4651 			}
4652 			else 
4653 				if (typeof selector == "String") {
4654 					elements = _engine(selector);
4655 					if(selector!=="" && selector!==null && elements.length==0){
4656             // throw exception
4657             throw "Exception while parsing the selector [" + selector + "]";
4658 					}
4659 					if (Array.isArray(elements)) {
4660 						nodeList = nodeList.concat(elements);
4661 					}
4662 					else {
4663 						nodeList.push(elements);
4664 					}
4665 				}
4666             return nodeList;
4667         },
4668         /**
4669          * Register another selector engine.
4670          * @param {String} name Name to identify the Engine.
4671          * @param {Function} adaptedFunction Function to adapt the main function of the engine.
4672          * @return {String} Return the identifier of registered engine.
4673          *  */
4674         registerEngine: function(name, adaptedFunction){
4675             if (typeof Engines[name] != 'undefined') {
4676                 //Warning: Parser with this identifier exists and will be overwritten
4677             }
4678             Engines[name] = adaptedFunction;
4679             return name;
4680         }
4681         
4682         
4683     };
4684 })();

4828

4845             this.pageX = pageX;
4846         }
4847         if (pageY !== 'undefined' && pageY !== null) {
4848             this.pageY = pageY;
4849         }
4850         if (radiusX !== 'undefined' && radiusX !== null) {
4851             this.radiusX = radiusX;
4852         }

4854             this.radiusY = radiusY;
4855         }
4856         if (rotationAngle !== 'undefined' && rotationAngle !== null) {
4857             this.rotationAngle = rotationAngle;
4858         }
4859         if (force !== 'undefined' && force !== null) {
4860             this.force = force;
4861         }
