4906         pageY: 0,
4907         /**
4908          * The radius of the ellipse which most closely circumscribes the touching area (e.g. finger, stylus) along the x-axis, in pixels of the same scale as screenX; 1 if no value is known. The value must be positive.
4909          * @type Number
4910          * @default 1
4911          */
4912         radiusX: 1,
4913         /**
4914          * The radius of the ellipse which most closely circumscribes the touching area (e.g. finger, stylus) along the y-axis, in pixels of the same scale as screenY; 1 if no value is known. The value must be positive.
4915          * @type Number
4916          * @default 1
4917          */
4918         radiusY: 1,
4919         /**
4920          * The angle (in degrees) that the ellipse described by radiusX and radiusY is rotated clockwise about its center; 0 if no value is known. The value must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than 90
4921          */
4922         rotationAngle: 0,
4923         /**
4924          * a relative value of pressure applied, in the range 0 to 1, where 0 is no pressure, and 1 is the highest level of pressure the touch device is capable of sensing; 0 if no value is known.
4925          * @type Float
4926          * @default 0
4927          */
4928         force: 0
4929     };
4930     
4931 	/**
4932 	 * EventObservation
4933 	 * @exports EventObservation as GeForMT.Observation.EventObservation
4934 	 * @class
4935 	 * @param {String} gestureId Identifier of the gesture
4936 	 * @param {Element} element Element node of the DOM tree
4937 	 * @param {Boolean} captureEvents Event flow: True for capturing or false for bubbling
4938 	 */
4939      function EventObservation(gestureId, element, captureEvents){
4940     
4941         this.gestureIdList = [gestureId];
4942         
4943         
4944         this.element = element;
4945         //console.debug(this.element);
4946         try {
4947             // touch events
4948             _addEventListener(this.element, 'touchstart', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHSTART),captureEvents);
4949             _addEventListener(this.element, 'touchend', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHEND),captureEvents);
4950             _addEventListener(this.element, 'touchmove', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHMOVE),captureEvents);
4951             _addEventListener(this.element, 'touchcancel', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHCANCEL),captureEvents);
4952             _addEventListener(this.element, 'touchenter', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHENTER),captureEvents);
4953             _addEventListener(this.element, 'touchleave', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHLEAVE),captureEvents);
4954             
4955             // mouse events
4956             _addEventListener(this.element, 'mousedown', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEDOWN),captureEvents);
4957             _addEventListener(this.element, 'mousemove', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEMOVE),captureEvents);
4958             _addEventListener(this.element, 'mouseup', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEUP),captureEvents);
4959             _addEventListener(this.element, 'mouseover', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEOVER),captureEvents);
4960             _addEventListener(this.element, 'mouseout', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEOUT),captureEvents);
4961         } 
4962         catch (e) {
4963             // throw own exception with additional information
4964             throw "Exception while adding event listener on element [" +
4965             this.element +
4966             "] of gesture with key [" +
4967             gestureId +
4968             "]: /n " +
4969             e;
4970         }
4971         
4972     }
4973     
4974     EventObservation.prototype = /** @lends GeForMT.Observation-EventObservation*/{
4975         /**
4976          * Subject to observe.
4977          *
4978          * @type element
4979          * @default null
4980          */
4981         element: null,
4982         
4983         /**
4984          * Gesture Identifier the observed subject belongs to.
4985          *
4986          * @type Array
4987          * @default null
4988          */
4989         gestureIdList: null,
4990         /**
4991          * Adds a gesture identifier to the gestureIdList in this observation.
4992          *
4993          * @param gestureId
4994          *            {String} The identifier of the gesture.
4995          */
4996         addGestureId: function(gestureId){
4997             this.gestureIdList.push(gestureId);
4998         },
4999         /**
5000          * Check if the gesture id is already registered in this observation.
5001          *
5002          * @param gestureId
5003          *            {String} The identifier of the gesture.
5004          * @return {Boolean} True, if gesture identifier already exists. False,
5005          *         if not.
5006          */
5007         gestureIdExists: function(gestureId){
5008             for (var key=0; key<this.gestureIdList.length;key++) {
5009                 if (this.gestureIdList[key] === gestureId) {
5010                     return true;
5011                 }
5012             }
5013             return false;
5014         },
5015         /**
5016          * Remove gesture from identifier list.
5017          * @param {String} gestureId Identifier of the gesture.
5018          */
5019         removeGestureId: function(gestureId){
5020         	for (var key=0; key<this.gestureIdList.length;key++) {
5021                 if (this.gestureIdList[key] == gestureId) {
5022                     this.gestureIdList.splice(key,1);
5023                     break;
5024                 }
5025             }
5026         },
5027         /**
5028          * This method has to be called before destroying this event observation.
5029          * It removes all event handler from the element.
5030          */
5031         finalize: function(){
5032         	// touch events
5033             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'touchstart', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHSTART));
5034             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'touchend', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHEND));
5035             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'touchmove', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHMOVE));
5036             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'touchcancel', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHCANCEL));
5037             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'touchenter', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHENTER));
5038             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'touchleave', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHLEAVE));
5039             
5040             // mouse events
5041             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'mousedown', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEDOWN));
5042             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'mousemove', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEMOVE));
5043             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'mouseup', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEUP));
5044             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'mouseover', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEOVER));
5045             _removeEventListener(this.element, 'mouseout', this._getEventHandler(EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEOUT));
5046  
5047         },
5048         /**
5049          * Returns the event handler by type.
5050          * See GeForMT.Observation.EVENT_TYPES getting the implemented event types.
5051          *
5052          * @private
5053          * @param eventType
5054          *            GeForMT.Observation.EVENT_TYPES
5055          * @return {Function} Returns the event handler or null if the eventType
5056          *         is unknown.
5057          */
5058         _getEventHandler: function(eventType){
5059             var context = this;
5060             var handler = null;
5061 			var i=0;
5062             
5063             switch (eventType) {
5064                 case EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHSTART:
5065                     handler = function(e){
5066                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5067                             e.preventDefault();
5068                         }
5069 						//create Contact Objects as representation of Touch
5070 						// this is required, because these objects are pooled from API
5071 						var contacts=[];
5072 						for(var i=0;i<e.touches.length;i++){
5073 							var touch=e.touches[i];
5074 							var contact=new Contact(touch.identifier, touch.screenX, touch.screenY, touch.clientX, touch.clientY, touch.pageX, touch.pageY, touch.radiusX, touch.radiusY, touch.rotationAngle, touch.force);
5075 							contacts.push(contact);
5076 						}
5077 						//e.touches=newTouches;
5078 						e.contacts=contacts;
5079                         e.relatedGestures = context.gestureIdList;
5080                         if (context === _documentEventObservation) {
5081                             _notifyAllDocumentEventListener('gesturestart', e);
5082                         }
5083                         else {
5084                             _notifyAllGestureEventListener('gesturestart', e);
5085                         }
5086                     };
5087                     break;
5088                 case EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHEND:
5089                     handler = function(e){
5090                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5091                             e.preventDefault();
5092                         }
5093 						//create Contact Objects as representation of Touch
5094 						// this is required, because these objects are pooled from API
5095 						var contacts=[];
5096 						for(var i=0;i<e.touches.length;i++){
5097 							var touch=e.touches[i];
5098 							var contact=new Contact(touch.identifier, touch.screenX, touch.screenY, touch.clientX, touch.clientY, touch.pageX, touch.pageY, touch.radiusX, touch.radiusY, touch.rotationAngle, touch.force);
5099 							contacts.push(contact);
5100 						}
5101 						//e.touches=newTouches;
5102 						e.contacts=contacts;
5103                         e.relatedGestures = context.gestureIdList;
5104                         if (context === _documentEventObservation) {
5105                             _notifyAllDocumentEventListener('gestureend', e);
5106                         }
5107                         else {
5108                             _notifyAllGestureEventListener('gestureend', e);
5109                         }
5110                         
5111                     };
5112                     break;
5113                 case EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHMOVE:
5114                     handler = function(e){
5115                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5116                             e.preventDefault();
5117                         }
5118 						//console.debug(e.touches[0].pageX);
5119 					//create Contact Objects as representation of Touch
5120 						// this is required, because these objects are pooled from API
5121                       var contacts=[];
5122 						for(var i=0;i<e.touches.length;i++){
5123 							var touch=e.touches[i];
5124 							var contact=new Contact(touch.identifier, touch.screenX, touch.screenY, touch.clientX, touch.clientY, touch.pageX, touch.pageY, touch.radiusX, touch.radiusY, touch.rotationAngle, touch.force);
5125 							contacts.push(contact);
5126 						}
5127 					//	console.debug(newTouches[0].pageX);
5128 						//e.touches=newTouches;
5129 						e.contacts=contacts;
5130                         e.relatedGestures = context.gestureIdList;
5131                         if (context === _documentEventObservation) {
5132                             _notifyAllDocumentEventListener('gesturechange', e);
5133                         }
5134                         else {
5135                             _notifyAllGestureEventListener('gesturechange', e);
5136                         }
5137 
5138                     };
5139                     break;
5140                 case EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHENTER:
5141                     handler = function(e){
5142                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5143                             e.preventDefault();
5144                         }
5145                        
5146                     };
5147                     break;
5148                 case EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHLEAVE:
5149                     handler = function(e){
5150                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5151                             e.preventDefault();
5152                         }
5153                        
5154                     };
5155                     break;
5156                 case EVENT_TYPES.TOUCHCANCEL:
5157                     handler = function(e){
5158                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5159                             e.preventDefault();
5160                         }
5161                     };
5162                     break;
5163                 case EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEDOWN:
5164                     handler = function(e){
5165                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5166                             e.preventDefault();
5167                         }
5168                         e.stopPropagation();
5169 
5170                         _createAndDispatchTouchEvent('touchstart', e);
5171                     // _notifyAllGestureEventListener('gesturestart', gestureEvent); 
5172                     };
5173                     break;
5174                 case EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEUP:
5175                     handler = function(e){
5176                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5177                             e.preventDefault();
5178                         }
5179                         e.stopPropagation();
5180                         //   var contacts = new ContactList([new Contact(null, e.screenX, e.screenY, e.clientX, e.clientY, null, null, null, null, null, null)]);
5181                         //  var gestureEvent = new GestureEvent(contacts, null, null, e.altKey, e.crtlKey, e.metaKey, e.shiftKey, e.button, e.target, e.currentTarget, e.relatedTarget, e.timestamp,e.type, e,context.gestureIdList);
5182                         _createAndDispatchTouchEvent('touchend', e);
5183                     // _notifyAllGestureEventListener('gestureend', gestureEvent);
5184                     };
5185                     break;
5186                 case EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEMOVE:
5187                     handler = function(e){
5188                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5189                             e.preventDefault();
5190                         }
5191                         e.stopPropagation();
5192                         _createAndDispatchTouchEvent('touchmove', e);
5193                     };
5194                     break;
5195                 case EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEOVER:
5196                     handler = function(e){
5197                         if (_preventDefault) {
5198                             e.preventDefault();
5199                         }
5200                         _createAndDispatchTouchEvent('touchenter', e);
5201                     };
5202                     break;
5203                 case EVENT_TYPES.MOUSEOUT:
5204                     handler = function(e){
5205                         if (_preventDefault && !(context === _documentEventObservation)) {
5206                             e.preventDefault();
5207                         }
5208                         _createAndDispatchTouchEvent('touchleave', e);
5209                     };
5210                     break;
5211                     
5212             }
5213             return handler;
5214         }
5215         
5216     };

5218     /**
5219      * Notify all registered gesture listener.
5220      * @param  {String} eventName Type name of the event.
5221      * @param  {UIEvent} event Adapted Touch Event.
5222      */
5223     function _notifyAllGestureEventListener(eventName, event){
5224         var handlerList = RegisteredGestureEventListener[eventName];
5225         var listLength = handlerList.length;
5226         for (var i = 0; i < listLength; i++) {
5227             var callback = handlerList[i];
5228             if (callback != 'undefined' && event.relatedGestures.length>0) {
5229                 callback(event);
5230             }
5231         }
5232     }
5233 	
5234 	    
5235     /**
5236      * Notify all registered document event listener.
5237      * @param  {String} eventName Type name of the event.
5238      * @param  {UIEvent} event Adapted Touch Event.
5239      */
5240     function _notifyAllDocumentEventListener(eventName, event){
5241         var handlerList = RegisteredDocumentEventListener[eventName];
5242         var listLength = handlerList.length;
5243         for (var i = 0; i < listLength; i++) {
5244             var callback = handlerList[i];
5245             if (callback != 'undefined') {
5246                 callback(event);
5247             }
5248         }
5249     }
5250     
5251     /**
5252      * Create and dispatch a TouchEvent to simulate a single touch with a mouse.
5253      * @param  {String} name Event type of event to dispatch.
5254      * @param  {MouseEvent} event Original event, that has to be adapted.
5255      */
5256     function _createAndDispatchTouchEvent(name, event){
5257         var srcEventName = event.type;
5258         // check that a mouse gesture starts
5259         if (srcEventName == 'mousedown') {
5260             this._mouseMoveEventEnabled = true;
5261             _mouseStrokeId++;
5262         }
5263         // check the end of a mouse gesture
5264         if (srcEventName == 'mouseup') {
5265             this._mouseMoveEventEnabled = false;
5266         }
5267         
5268         // prevent mousemove events beyond a gesture (that means events for positioning the cursor without clicking are excluded)
5269         if ((srcEventName == 'mousemove' || srcEventName == 'mouseover' || srcEventName == 'mouseout') && !this._mouseMoveEventEnabled) {
5270             return;
5271         }
5272         
5273         // create a custom event with touch event interface structure by the W3C
5274         var touchevent = document.createEvent('CustomEvent');
5275         touchevent.initEvent(name, true, false);
5276         var touch = {
5277             identifier: _mouseStrokeId,
5278             pageX: event.pageX,
5279             pageY: event.pageY,
5280             screenX: event.screenX,
5281             screenY: event.screenY,
5282             clientX: event.clientX,
5283             clientY: event.clientY,
5284             radiusX: 1,
5285             radiusX: 1,
5286             rotationAngle: 0,
5287             force: 0
5288         };
5289         var touches = [touch];
5290         touchevent.ctrlKey = event.ctrlKey;
5291         touchevent.shiftKey = event.shiftKey;
5292         touchevent.metaKey = event.metaKey;
5293         touchevent.touches = touches;
5294         touchevent.targetTouches = touches;
5295         touchevent.changedTouches = touches;
5296         touchevent.sourceEvent = event;
5297         
5298         // dispatch the created event to simulate a touch event
5299         if (event.target) {
5300             //	window.document.dispatchEvent(touchevent);
5301             event.target.dispatchEvent(touchevent);
5302         }
5303         else {
5304             window.document.dispatchEvent(touchevent);
5305         }
5306     }
5307     
5308 	/**
5309 	 * Helper method for cross-browser registering of event listeners.
5310 	 * @param {Element} element
5311 	 * @param {String} eventName
5312 	 * @param {Function} handler
5313 	 * @param {Boolean} captureEvents
5314 	 */
5315     function _addEventListener(element, eventName, handler, captureEvents){
5316         if (document.addEventListener) {
5317             // W3C
5318             element.addEventListener(eventName, handler, captureEvents);
5319         }
5320         else 
5321             if (document.attachEvent) {
5322                 // IE
5323                 element.attachEvent('on' + eventName, handler);
5324             }
5325             else {
5326                 element['on' + eventName] = handler;
5327             }
5328     }
5329     /**
5330 	 * Helper method for cross-browser removing of event listeners.
5331 	 * @param {Element} element
5332 	 * @param {String} eventName
5333 	 * @param {Function} handler
5334 	 */
5335      function _removeEventListener(element, eventName, handler){
5336         if (document.removeEventListener) {
5337             // W3C
5338             element.removeEventListener(eventName, handler);
5339         }
5340         else 
5341             if (document.detachEvent) {
5342                 // IE
5343                 element.detachEvent('on' + eventName, handler);
5344             }
5345             else {
5346                 element['on' + eventName] = null;
5347             }
5348     }
5349     
5350     return {
5351         /**
5352          * Initialize observation module.
5353          *
5354          * @param preventDefault
5355          *            {Boolean} Set to true for preventing the default behaviour
5356          *            on all events.
5357          */
5358         init: function(preventDefault){
5359             _preventDefault = preventDefault;
5360             _registeredGestureEventListener = [];
5361             _registeredEventObservations = [];
5362             
5363             //create EventObservation on 'document'-Object to get feedback on the entire interface
5364             _documentEventObservation = new EventObservation("feedback", document,true);
5365             
5366         },
5367         /**
5368          * Register an observation on the given list of elements get informed
5369          * about interaction on them.
5370          *
5371          * @param gestureId
5372          *            {String} Identifier of the gesture.
5373          * @param elementList
5374          *            {Array} List of all elements on which the events will be
5375          *            registered.
5376          */
5377         addEventObservation: function(gestureId, elementList){
5378             for (var i = 0; i < elementList.length; i++) {
5379                 var alreadyRegisteredObservation = this.getObservationByElement(elementList[i]);
5380                 if (alreadyRegisteredObservation !== null) {
5381                     if (!alreadyRegisteredObservation.gestureIdExists(gestureId)) {
5382                         alreadyRegisteredObservation.addGestureId(gestureId);
5383                     }
5384                 }
5385                 else {
5386                     _registeredEventObservations.push(new EventObservation(gestureId,elementList[i],false));
5387                 }
5388             }
5389             //console.debug(_registeredEventObservations);
5390         },
5391         /**
5392          * Returns the observer that is already registered on the given element
5393          * node or null if it's not.
5394          *
5395          * @param {Element} element
5396          * @return GeForMT.Observation.EventObserver
5397          */
5398         getObservationByElement: function(element){
5399         
5400             var observationListLength = _registeredEventObservations.length;
5401             for (var i = 0; i < observationListLength; i++) {
5402                 var registeredObservation = _registeredEventObservations[i];
5403                 if (registeredObservation.element === element) {
5404                     return registeredObservation;
5405                 }
5406                 
5407             }
5408             return null;
5409         },
5410         /**
5411          * Removes a gesture identifier from an event observation.
5412          * @param {String} gestureId Identifier of the gesture, that has to be removed.
5413          */
5414          removeGestureFromEventObservation: function(gestureId){
5415          	var observationListLength = _registeredEventObservations.length;
5416          	
5417             for (var i in _registeredEventObservations) {
5418             	 var registeredObservation = _registeredEventObservations[i];       	 
5419                   registeredObservation.removeGestureId(gestureId);
5420             	 if(registeredObservation.gestureIdList.length===0){
5421             	 registeredObservation.finalize();
5422             	  _registeredEventObservations.splice(i,1);
5423             	  if(_registeredEventObservations.length==1){
5424             	  	_registeredEventObservations=[];
5425             	  }
5426             	 }
5427             }
5428          },
5429         /**
5430          * Register listener objects that wants to be notified about all interaction
5431          * events.
5432 		 * @param {String} eventName
5433 		 * @param {Function} callback
5434          */
5435         registerGestureEventListener: function(eventType, callback){
5436         
5437             if (typeof RegisteredGestureEventListener[eventType] != 'undefined') {
5438                 RegisteredGestureEventListener[eventType].push(callback);
5439             }
5440             
5441         },
5442 		/**
5443          * Remove listener that don't want to be notified about all interaction
5444          * events anymore.
5445 		 * @param {String} eventName
5446 		 * @param {Function} callback
5447 		 */
5448         removeGestureEventListener: function(eventType, callback){
5449         
5450             if (typeof RegisteredGestureEventListener[eventType] != 'undefined') {
5451                 var list = RegisteredGestureEventListener[eventType];
5452                 for (var i = 0; i < list.length; i++) {
5453                     if (list[i] === callback) {
5454                         list.splice(i, 1);
5455                     }
5456                 }
5457             }
5458             
5459         },
5460         
5461 		/**
5462 		 * Register listener objects that wants to be notified about
5463          * events that are registered on document object. (only on document)
5464 		 * @param {String} eventName
5465 		 * @param {Function} callback
5466 		 */
5467         registerDocumentEventListener: function(eventName, callback){
5468         
5469             if (typeof RegisteredDocumentEventListener[eventName] != 'undefined') {
5470                 RegisteredDocumentEventListener[eventName].push(callback);
5471             }
5472             
5473         },
5474 		/**
5475          * Remove listener that don't want to be notified about
5476          * events on document object anymore. (only on document)
5477 		 * @param {String} eventName
5478 		 * @param {Function} callback
5479 		 */
5480         removeDocumentEventListener: function(eventName, callback){
5481         
5482             if (typeof RegisteredDocumentEventListener[eventName] != 'undefined') {
5483                 var list = RegisteredDocumentEventListener[eventName];
5484                 for (var i = 0; i < list.length; i++) {
5485                     if (list[i] === callback) {
5486                         list.splice(i, 1);
5487                     }
5488                 }
5489             }
5490             
5491         }
5492     };
5493 })();
5494 /**
5495  * @namespace
5496  * VisualFeedback module
5497  */
5498 GeForMT.VisualFeedback = (function(){
5499     /**
5500      * The observation module GeForMT.Observation
5501      * @type GeForMT.Observation
5502      * @default null
5503      * @private
5504      */
5505     var _observationModule = null;
5506     /**
5507      * The observation module GeForMT.Observation
5508      * @type GeForMT.GestureRecognition
5509      * @default null
5510      * @private
5511      */
5512     var _recognitionModule = null;
5513     /**
5514      * Canvas element representing the feedback layer. Shows current contacts.
5515      * @type Element
5516      * @default null
5517      * @private
5518      */
5519     var _feedbackCanvas = null;
5520     /**
5521      * Canvas element representing a second feedback layer. Shows saved gesture pathes.
5522      * @type Element
5523      * @default null
5524      * @private
5525      */
5526     var _pathesFeedbackCanvas = null;

5603     /**
5604      * State that represents the global setting for drawing a feedback.
5605      * True if feedback should be displayed.

5610     var _feedbackEnabled = false;
5611     /**
5612      * Create two canvas elements on top of the web content to draw visual feedback on it.
5613      * One canvas for updating current position of contacts, the other canvas for drawing gesture pathes on it.
5614      * Requirements for this feature:
5615      * 1. This feature requires HTML5.
5616      * 2. The browser must support the CSS property 'pointer-events'.
5617      * @private
5618      */
5619     function _createFeedbackEnvironment(){
5620         _feedbackCanvas = document.createElement("canvas");
5621         var canvasStyle = _feedbackCanvas.style;
5622         
5623         /*	canvasStyle.borderStyle = "solid";
5624          canvasStyle.borderColor = "black";
5625          canvasStyle.borderWidth = "1";*/
5626         // set position and size of the canvas
5627         canvasStyle.zIndex = "10000";
5628         canvasStyle.position = "absolute";
5629         canvasStyle.top = "0";
5630         canvasStyle.left = "0";
5631         canvasStyle.right = "0";
5632         canvasStyle.bottom = "0";
5633         // _feedbackCanvas.width = (window.innerWidth !== 0) ? window.innerWidth : 0;
5634         // _feedbackCanvas.height = (window.innerHeight !== 0) ? window.innerHeight : 0;
5635         
5636         _feedbackCanvas.width = (document.documentElement.scrollWidth !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollWidth : 0;
5637         _feedbackCanvas.height = (document.documentElement.scrollHeight !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollHeight : 0;
5638         
5639         _pathesFeedbackCanvas = document.createElement("canvas");
5640         var pathesCanvasStyle = _pathesFeedbackCanvas.style;
5641         
5642         /*	canvasStyle.borderStyle = "solid";
5643          canvasStyle.borderColor = "black";
5644          canvasStyle.borderWidth = "1";*/
5645         // set position and size of the canvas
5646         pathesCanvasStyle.zIndex = "10000";
5647         pathesCanvasStyle.position = "absolute";
5648         pathesCanvasStyle.top = "0";
5649         pathesCanvasStyle.left = "0";
5650         pathesCanvasStyle.right = "0";
5651         pathesCanvasStyle.bottom = "0";
5652         // _feedbackCanvas.width = (window.innerWidth !== 0) ? window.innerWidth : 0;
5653         // _feedbackCanvas.height = (window.innerHeight !== 0) ? window.innerHeight : 0;
5654         
5655         _pathesFeedbackCanvas.width = (document.documentElement.scrollWidth !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollWidth : 0;
5656         _pathesFeedbackCanvas.height = (document.documentElement.scrollHeight !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollHeight : 0;
5657         
5658         
5659         window.onresize = function(){
5660             _feedbackCanvas.width = (document.documentElement.scrollWidth !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollWidth : 0;
5661             _feedbackCanvas.height = (document.documentElement.scrollHeight !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollHeight : 0;
5662             
5663             _pathesFeedbackCanvas.width = (document.documentElement.scrollWidth !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollWidth : 0;
5664             _pathesFeedbackCanvas.height = (document.documentElement.scrollHeight !== 0) ? document.documentElement.scrollHeight : 0;
5665             
5666         };
5667         
5668         
5669         // make the feedback layers "click-through"
5670         if (typeof canvasStyle.pointerEvents !== 'undefined') {
5671             canvasStyle.pointerEvents = "none";
5672             pathesCanvasStyle.pointerEvents = "none";
5673         }
5674         
5675         // append default text 
5676         var canvasDefaultText = document.createTextNode("Sorry, the feedback feature requires HTML5 where canvas is implemented.");
5677         _feedbackCanvas.appendChild(canvasDefaultText);
5678         _pathesFeedbackCanvas.appendChild(canvasDefaultText);
5679         
5680         // get drawing context
5681         _feedbackCanvasContext = _feedbackCanvas.getContext("2d");
5682         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext = _pathesFeedbackCanvas.getContext("2d");
5683         
5684         // set timer for redrawing in intervals
5685         _updateTimer = setInterval(_updateVisualFeedback, _updateInterval);
5686     }

5688     /**
5689      * Integrate the feedback layers into the website and register for events.
5690      * @private
5691      */
5692     function _addVisualFeedback(){
5693         document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0].appendChild(_feedbackCanvas);
5694         document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0].appendChild(_pathesFeedbackCanvas);
5695         
5696         //register for interaction events
5697         _observationModule.registerDocumentEventListener('gesturestart', _gesturestart);
5698         _observationModule.registerDocumentEventListener('gesturechange', _gesturechange);
5699         _observationModule.registerDocumentEventListener('gestureend', _gestureend);
5700         
5701         //register for recognition events
5702         _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener('recognitionstarted', _recognitionstarted);
5703         _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener('recognitionfailed', _recognitionfailed);
5704         _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener('gesturerecognized', _recognitionsuccess);
5705         _recognitionModule.registerGestureRecognitionEventListener('candidatesrecognized', _candidatesrecognized);
5706     }
5707     /**
5708      * Remove feedback layers and events from the website.
5709      * @private
5710      */
5711     function _removeVisualFeedback(){
5712         _observationModule.removeDocumentEventListener('gesturestart', _gesturestart);
5713         _observationModule.removeDocumentEventListener('gesturechange', _gesturechange);
5714         _observationModule.removeDocumentEventListener('gestureend', _gestureend);
5715         
5716         _recognitionModule.removeGestureRecognitionEventListener('recognitionstarted', _recognitionstarted);
5717         _recognitionModule.removeGestureRecognitionEventListener('recognitionfailed', _recognitionfailed);
5718         _recognitionModule.removeGestureRecognitionEventListener('gesturerecognized', _recognitionsuccess);
5719         _recognitionModule.removeGestureRecognitionEventListener('candidatesrecognized', _candidatesrecognized);
5720         
5721         document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0].removeChild(_feedbackCanvas);
5722         document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0].removeChild(_pathesFeedbackCanvas);
5723     }
5724     /**
5725      * Updating the feedback layer by redrawing the current touch points (contacts) on the canvas.
5726      * This functions uses the _feedbackCanvas to draw current contact points and _feedbackCanvasContext to draw gesture pathes.
5727      * @private
5728      * */
5729     function _updateVisualFeedback(){
5730         if (_busy) 
5731             return;
5732         //return;
5733         _busy = true;
5734         
5735         
5736         _feedbackCanvasContext.clearRect(0, 0, _feedbackCanvas.width, _feedbackCanvas.height);
5737         
5738         var tl = _touches.length;
5739         for (var i = 0; i < tl; i++) {
5740         
5741             // get coordinates
5742             var touch = _touches[i];
5743             var id = touch.identifier;
5744             var x = touch.pageX;
5745             var y = touch.pageY;
5746             
5747            
5748             // save touches to visualize the gesture path
5749             if (_gesturePathes.length === 0) {
5750                 // build gesture pathes
5751                 _gesturePathes.push([{
5752                     id: id,
5753                     pageX: x,
5754                     pageY: y
5755                 }]);
5756                 
5757             }
5758             else {
5759                 var pathIdExist = false;
5760                 // try assigning touches
5761                 for (var gp = 0; gp < _gesturePathes.length; gp++) {
5762                     var gesturePath = _gesturePathes[gp];
5763                     if (gesturePath[0].id === id) {
5764                         pathIdExist = true;
5765                         var gpx = x;
5766                         var gpy = y;
5767                         
5768                         var nextGpx = gesturePath[gesturePath.length - 1].pageX;
5769                         var nextGpy = gesturePath[gesturePath.length - 1].pageY;
5770                         
5771                         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext.beginPath();
5772                         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext.strokeStyle = 'rgba(0, 0, 200, 0.5)';
5773                         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext.lineWidth = 4;
5774                         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext.moveTo(nextGpx, nextGpy);
5775                         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext.lineTo(gpx, gpy);
5776                         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext.stroke();
5777                         _pathesFeedbackCanvasContext.closePath();
5778                         
5779                         gesturePath.push({
5780                             id: id,
5781                             pageX: x,
5782                             pageY: y
5783                         });
5784                     }
5785                     else {
5786                     
5787                     }
5788                 }
5789                 if (!pathIdExist) {
5790                     _gesturePathes.push([{
5791                         id: id,
5792                         pageX: x,
5793                         pageY: y
5794                     }]);
5795                 }
5796             }
5797             
5798             // draw circle for current touch point
5799             _feedbackCanvasContext.beginPath();
5800             _feedbackCanvasContext.arc(x, y, 30, 0, 2 * Math.PI, true);
5801             _feedbackCanvasContext.closePath();
5802             _feedbackCanvasContext.fillStyle = "rgba(0, 0, 200, 0.2)";
5803             _feedbackCanvasContext.fill();
5804             
5805             _feedbackCanvasContext.lineWidth = 2.0;
5806             _feedbackCanvasContext.strokeStyle = "rgba(0, 0, 200, 0.8)";
5807             _feedbackCanvasContext.stroke();
5808         }
5809         _busy = false;
5810         
5811     }

5925 /**
5926  * @namespace GestureRecognizer module
5927  */
5928 GeForMT.GestureRecognition = (function(){
5929 
5930     /**
5931      *	Holds a list for a specific event of this module with callback methods of listeners.
5932      *	Listeners must register for these events via API method.
5933      *
5934      *  Possible event types:
5935      *  'recognitionstarted': Event if recognition processor begins to process input data.;
5936      *  'recognitionfailed': Event if recognition processor couldn't recognize any gesture.;
5937      *  'gesturerecognized': Event if gesture has been recognized.;
5938      *  'candidatesrecognized': Event if gesture has been recognized but further gestures are expected.
5939      *	@type Object
5940      */
5941     var GestureRecognitionEventListener = {
5942         recognitionstarted: [],
5943         recognitionfailed: [],
5944         candidatesrecognized: [],
5945         gesturerecognized: []
5946     
5947     };
5948     
5949     /**
5950      * Registered module handling the gesture model as database for gesture
5951      * recognition.
5952      *
5953      * @type GeForMT.GestureModel
5954      * @default null
5955      * @private
5956      */
5957     var _gestureModelModule = null;
5958     /**
5959      * Template builder module.
5960      * @type GeForMT.TemplateBuilder
5961      * @default null
5962      * @private
5963      */
5964     var _templateBuilder = null;
5965     /**
5966      * Recognition task manager, that manages the recognition process.
5967      *
5968      * @type GeForMT.GestureRecognition.RecognitionTaskManager
5969      * @default null
5970      */
5971     var _recognitionProcessManager = null;
5972     /**
5973      * TimeStamp of the first received touch event.
5974      * @default null
5975      */
5976     var _firstEventTimeStamp = null;
5977     /**
5978      * Contiguity interval in milliseconds. Represents the time interval to
5979      * expected gesture events and assert the official end of a complex
5980      * gestures.
5981      * @type Number
5982      * @default 1000
5983      */
5984     var _gestureContiguityInterval = 1000;
5985     /**
5986      * Set contiguity interval with the timeout function of JavaScript. This
5987      * Timeout is needed to assert the official end of a gesture.
5988      * @type Object
5989      * @default null
5990      */
5991     var _gestureContiguityIntervalTimer = null;
5992     
5993     /**
5994      * Event handler that listens to 'gesturestart' events of the Observation
5995      * module.
5996      *
5997      * @param {UIEvent}
5998      *            e Touch event.
5999      */
6000     function _gesturestart(e){
6001         // e.stopPropagation();
6002         // clear contiguity timer if set
6003         if (_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer !== null) {
6004             window.clearTimeout(_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer);
6005         }
6006         
6007         // check timestamp to recognize the start of this gesture
6008         if (_firstEventTimeStamp === null) {
6009             // set timestamp
6010             _firstEventTimeStamp = e.timeStamp;
6011         }
6012         
6013         //task creation at first touch point of a gesture
6014         if (_firstEventTimeStamp == e.timeStamp) {
6015         
6016             // create recognition task  
6017             _recognitionProcessManager.createEventProfiles(e);
6018             
6019             // start recognizing
6020             if (!_recognitionProcessManager.isWorking) {
6021                 // a gesture starts with the first touch event
6022                 _recognitionProcessManager.start();
6023             }
6024         }
6025         else {
6026             _recognitionProcessManager.updateEventProfiles(e);
6027         }
6028         
6029     }
6030     /**
6031      * Event handler that listens to 'gesturechange' events of the Observation module.
6032      * @param {Event} e Touch event.
6033      */
6034     function _gesturechange(e){
6035         //e.stopPropagation();
6036         // reset contiguity interval
6037         if (_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer !== null) {
6038             window.clearTimeout(_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer);
6039         }
6040         _gestureContiguityIntervalTimer = window.setTimeout(_cancelRecognitionProcess, _gestureContiguityInterval);
6041         
6042         // update event profile
6043         _recognitionProcessManager.updateEventProfiles(e);
6044         
6045     }
6046     /**
6047      * Event handler that listens to 'gestureend' events of the Observation module.
6048      * @param {Event} e Touch event.
6049      */
6050     function _gestureend(e){
6051         e.stopPropagation();
6052         // update event profile
6053         _recognitionProcessManager.updateEventProfiles(e);
6054         
6055         // reset contiguity interval
6056         if (_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer !== null) {
6057             window.clearTimeout(_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer);
6058         }
6059         _gestureContiguityIntervalTimer = window.setTimeout(_cancelRecognitionProcess, _gestureContiguityInterval);
6060         // console.debug(_recognitionProcessManager.eventProfiles);
6061     }
6062     /**
6063      * Stop and reset the recognition process including the recognition
6064      * task manager and all corresponding components and tasks.
6065      * This function is called when a timeout occurs caused by the contiguity interval timer.
6066      */
6067     function _cancelRecognitionProcess(){
6068         _firstEventTimeStamp = null;
6069         window.clearTimeout(_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer);
6070         
6071         if (_recognitionProcessManager.isWorking) {
6072             //check for noted already recognized gestures
6073             //console.debug(_recognitionProcessManager.recognizedGestures);
6074             if (_recognitionProcessManager.recognizedGestures.length > 0) {
6075                 var gestureRecognizedEvent = _recognitionProcessManager.recognizedGestures[0];
6076                 /*
6077                  * var gestureId = gestureRecognizedEvent.identifier; var
6078                  * gesture = _gestureModelModule.getGestureById(gestureId);
6079                  * gesture.handler(gestureRecognizedEvent);
6080                  */
6081                 // notify listeners that gesture has been recognized
6082                 var callbacks = GestureRecognitionEventListener.gesturerecognized;
6083                 for (var i = 0; i < callbacks.length; i++) {
6084                     callbacks[i](gestureRecognizedEvent);
6085                 }
6086             }
6087             else {
6088             
6089                 //create GestureRecognitionFailedEvent
6090                 var recognitionFailedEvent = new GestureRecognitionFailedEvent();
6091                 // notify listeners that recognition failed
6092                 var callbacks = GestureRecognitionEventListener.recognitionfailed;
6093                 for (var i = 0; i < callbacks.length; i++) {
6094                     callbacks[i](recognitionFailedEvent);
6095                 }
6096             }
6097         }
6098         
6099         //reset recognition processor
6100         _recognitionProcessManager.reset();
6101         console.debug("Recognition stopped.");
6102     }
6103

6105      * Constructor of the recognition failed event
6106      * @class
6107      */
6108     function GestureRecognitionFailedEvent(){
6109     
6110     }
6111     GestureRecognitionFailedEvent.prototype =/*@lends*/ {};
6112     
6113     /**
6114      * Event interface of the recognitionstarted event.
6115      * @class
6116      */
6117     function GestureRecognitionStartedEvent(){
6118     
6119     }
6120     GestureRecognitionStartedEvent.prototype =/*@lends*/ {};
6121     
6122     /**
6123      * Event interface of the candidatesrecognized event.
6124      * @param {Array}
6125      *            candidateIds List of candidates.
6126      */
6127     function GestureRecognitionCandidatesEvent(candidateIds){
6128         this.candidates = candidateIds;
6129     }
6130     GestureRecognitionCandidatesEvent.prototype =/*@lends*/ {
6131         /**
6132          * List of candidates, represented by their identifier.
6133          * @type Array
6134          * @default empty array
6135          */
6136         candidates: []
6137     };
6138     
6139     /**
6140      * Event interface gesturerecognized event.
6141      * @param {String} identifier Identifier of the gesture
6142      * @param {GeForMT.GestureModel.Gesture} model
6143      * @param {Array} eventProfileHistory Nested lists of all events representing the gesture. Structure: The list contains gesture sequences. Every sequence represents a sequentially performed gesture. A sequence is a list of events that occured while performing the gesture.
6144      * @param {Array} gesturePathes Nested list of templates representing the gesture. Structure: The list contains gesture sequences. Every sequence represents a sequentially performed gesture. A sequence is a list of template objects (type GeForMT.TemplateBuilder.Template). Every template represents a single stroke. More than one template in the sequence means, that a Multitouch gesture has been performed.
6145      */
6146     function GestureRecognizedEvent(identifier, model, eventProfileHistory, gesturePathes){
6147     
6148         var currentStrokeEventProfile = eventProfileHistory[eventProfileHistory.length - 1];
6149         this.currentEvent = currentStrokeEventProfile[currentStrokeEventProfile.length - 1];
6150         this.identifier = identifier;
6151         this.events = eventProfileHistory;
6152         this.pathes = gesturePathes;
6153         this.expr = model.expr;
6154         this.online = model.online;
6155         this.target = this.currentEvent.target;
6156         
6157         var gestureStartEvent = currentStrokeEventProfile[0];
6158         var lastEvent = this.currentEvent;
6159         this.duration = (lastEvent.timeStamp / 1000) -
6160         (gestureStartEvent.timeStamp / 1000);
6161         
6162     }
6163     GestureRecognizedEvent.prototype = /*@lends*/ {
6164         /**
6165          * Last Event, that has been recognized.
6166          * @type UIEvent
6167          * @default null
6168          */
6169         currentEvent: null,
6170         /**
6171          * Target of current event.
6172          * @type Element
6173          * @default null
6174          */
6175         target: null,
6176         /**
6177          * List of lists containing all events of a gesture.
6178          * @type Array
6179          * @default []
6180          */
6181         events: [],
6182         /**
6183          * List of lists of template objects representing the pathes of the performed gesture.
6184          * @type Array
6185          * @default []
6186          */
6187         pathes: [],
6188         /**

6499             var callbacks = GestureRecognitionEventListener.gesturerecognized;
6500             for (var i = 0; i < callbacks.length; i++) {

6502             }

6505             if (!model.online) {

6508                 this.reset();
6509             }
6510             else {

6512                     _firstEventTimeStamp = null;
6513                     window.clearTimeout(_gestureContiguityIntervalTimer);
6514                     this.reset();
6515                 }
6516             }
