7276         /**
7277          * Gesture recognition algorithm based on '$1-Recognizer' by WOBBROCK et al. and 'Protractor' by LI.
7278          * Recognizes unistroke gesture ist adapted for multitouch gesture recognition.
7279          * @param {Boolean} useProtractor Set true, if you want to use protractor as recognition strategy.
7280          * @param {Number} numberOfPoints Number of points for resampling.
7281          * @param {Number} squareSize Init square size.
7282          * @param {Number} recognitionThreshold Init a recognition threshold.
7283          * @class
7284          */
7285         function DollarRecognizer(useProtractor, numberOfPoints, squareSize, recognitionThreshold){
7286             if (typeof useProtractor !== 'undefined' && useProtractor !== null) {
7287                 this.useProtractor = useProtractor;
7288             }
7289             if (typeof numberOfPoints !== 'undefined' &&
7290             numberOfPoints !== null) {
7291                 this.numberOfPoints = numberOfPoints;
7292             }
7293             if (typeof squareSize !== 'undefined' && squareSize !== null) {
7294                 this.squareSize = squareSize;
7295             }
7296             if (typeof recognitionThreshold !== 'undefined' &&
7297             recognitionThreshold !== null) {
7298                 if (this.useProtractor) {
7299                     this.protractorRecognitionThreshold = recognitionThreshold;
7300                 }
7301                 else {
7302                     this.dollarOneRecognitionThreshold = recognitionThreshold;
7303                 }
7304             }
7305             this.angleRange = this._deg2Rad(45.0);
7306             this.anglePrecision = this._deg2Rad(2.0);
7307         }
7308         
7309         DollarRecognizer.prototype = /*@lends*/ {
7310             /**
7311              * If true, Protractor algorithm is used. Else $1 recognizer algorithm of Wobbrock et al. is used.
7312              */
7313             useProtractor: false,
7314             /**
7315              * Maximum of average distance where a gesture can be recognized.
7316              * This restriction is necessary since $1 and Proctractor are calculating the best fit.
7317              * @type Number
7318              * @default 0.6
7319              */
7320             protractorRecognitionThreshold: 0.6,
7321             /**
7322              * Maximum of average distance where a gesture can be recognized.
7323              * This restriction is necessary since $1 and Proctractor are calculating the best fit.
7324              * @type Number
7325              * @default 50.0
7326              */
7327             dollarOneRecognitionThreshold: 50.0,
7328             /**
7329              * Number of points for resampling.
7330              * @type Number
7331              * @default 64
7332              */
7333             numberOfPoints: 64,
7334             /**
7335              * Square size.
7336              * @type Number
7337              * @default 250.0
7338              */
7339             squareSize: 250.0,
7340             /**
7341              * Threshold to recognize unidimensional gestures.
7342              * // customize to desired gesture set (usually 0.20-0.35)
7343              * @type Number
7344              * @default 20.0
7345              */
7346             oneDThreshold: 0.20,
7347             /**
7348              * Reference point represented by x and y coordinate.
7349              * @type Object
7350              * @default x=0 and y=0
7351              */
7352             origin: {
7353                 x: 0,
7354                 y: 0
7355             },
7356             /**
7357              * Diagonal of the square size.
7358              * @type Number
7359              */
7360             diagonal: Math.sqrt(this.squareSize * this.squareSize +
7361             this.squareSize * this.squareSize),
7362             /**
7363              * Half diagonal of the square size.
7364              * @type Number
7365              */
7366             halfDiagonal: 0.5 * this.diagonal,
7367             /**
7368              * Angle range.
7369              * @type Number
7370              * @default null
7371              */
7372             angleRange: null,
7373             /**
7374              * Angle precision.
7375              * @type Number
7376              * @default null
7377              */
7378             anglePrecision: null,
7379             /**
7380              * Golden Ratio.
7381              * @type Number
7382              */
7383             phi: 0.5 * (-1.0 + Math.sqrt(5.0)),
7384             /**
7385              * Main function of this recognition strategy.
7386              * @param {Object} performedGesturePathes
7387              * @param {Object} candidateGestures
7388              * @return {Object} Recognized gestures. Structure: (gestureId => optionIndex,..)
7389              */
7390             recognize: function(performedGesturePathes, candidateGestures){
7391                 var candidateGestureKeys = Object.keys(candidateGestures);
7392                 // calculate minimal distance between template and candidate
7393                 var b = +Infinity;
7394                 var t = 0;
7395                 // dList contains calculated distances corresponding to
7396                 // priorityList
7397                 var dList = [];
7398                 // distances data structure will be overwritten with calculated
7399                 // distances
7400                 var distances = {};
7401                 var d;
7402                 // each relevant gesture of priority list
7403                 for (var i = 0; i < candidateGestureKeys.length; i++) {
7404                     var candidateId = candidateGestureKeys[i];
7405                     var candidate = candidateGestures[candidateId];
7406                     var optionKeys = Object.keys(candidate);
7407                     var options = candidateGestures[candidateId];
7408                     distances[candidateId] = {};
7409                     
7410                     for (var o = 0; o < optionKeys.length; o++) {
7411                         var atomicGestures = options[optionKeys[o]];
7412                         distances[candidateId][optionKeys[o]] = +Infinity;
7413                         var averageDistanceOfSynchrounousperformedGestures = null;
7414                         for (var ag = 0; ag < atomicGestures.length; ag++) {
7415                             var atomicGesture = atomicGestures[ag];
7416                             var atomicGestureVariants = atomicGestures[ag].templates;
7417                             var performedPathes = performedGesturePathes[candidateId];
7418                             var performedGestureVectors;
7419                             var performedGesturePoints;
7420                             
7421                             var bestFitDistanceOfPerformedPath = +Infinity;
7422                             for (var pg = 0; pg < performedPathes.length; pg++) {
7423                                 if (this.useProtractor) {
7424                                     if (atomicGesture.rotationInvariant) {
7425                                         performedGestureVectors = this.getNormalizedVectors(performedPathes[pg], true);
7426                                     }
7427                                     else {
7428                                         performedGestureVectors = this.getNormalizedVectors(performedPathes[pg], false);
7429                                     }
7430                                 }
7431                                 else {
7432                                     if (atomicGesture.rotationInvariant) {
7433                                         performedGesturePoints = this.getNormalizedPoints(performedPathes[pg], true);
7434                                     }
7435                                     else {
7436                                         performedGesturePoints = this.getNormalizedPoints(performedPathes[pg], false);
7437                                     }
7438                                 }
7439                                 
7440                                 // var atomicGestureVariants =
7441                                 // atomicGesture.templates;
7442                                 // every variant of this atomic gesture
7443                                 var minVariantDistance = +Infinity;
7444                                 for (var v = 0; v < atomicGestureVariants.length; v++) {
7445                                     var variant = atomicGestureVariants[v];
7446                                     var variantVectors;
7447                                     var variantPoints;
7448                                     
7449                                     if (this.useProtractor) {
7450                                         if (atomicGesture.rotationInvariant) {
7451                                             variantVectors = this.getNormalizedVectors(variant, true);
7452                                         }
7453                                         else {
7454                                             variantVectors = this.getNormalizedVectors(variant, false);
7455                                         }
7456                                     }
7457                                     else {
7458                                         if (atomicGesture.rotationInvariant) {
7459                                         
7460                                             variantPoints = this.getNormalizedPoints(variant, true);
7461                                             
7462                                         }
7463                                         else {
7464                                             variantPoints = this.getNormalizedPoints(variant, false);
7465                                         }
7466                                     }
7467                                     if (this.useProtractor) {
7468                                         d = this.optimalCosineDistance(variantVectors, performedGestureVectors);
7469                                     }
7470                                     else {
7471                                         // Golden Section Search (original $1)
7472                                         d = this.distanceAtBestAngle(performedGesturePoints, variantPoints, -this.angleRange, +this.angleRange, this.anglePrecision);
7473                                     }
7474                                     if (d < minVariantDistance) {
7475                                         minVariantDistance = d;
7476                                     }
7477                                 }
7478                                 if (minVariantDistance < bestFitDistanceOfPerformedPath) {
7479                                     bestFitDistanceOfPerformedPath = minVariantDistance;
7480                                     
7481                                 }
7482                             }
7483                             
7484                             if (averageDistanceOfSynchrounousperformedGestures == null) {
7485                                 averageDistanceOfSynchrounousperformedGestures = bestFitDistanceOfPerformedPath;
7486                             }
7487                             else {
7488                                 averageDistanceOfSynchrounousperformedGestures = averageDistanceOfSynchrounousperformedGestures +
7489                                 bestFitDistanceOfPerformedPath;
7490                             }
7491                             
7492                         }
7493                         
7494                         d = averageDistanceOfSynchrounousperformedGestures;
7495                         
7496                         // overwrite distance model
7497                         var distanceModel = distances[candidateId][optionKeys[o]];
7498                         if (typeof distanceModel === 'number') {
7499                             if (d < distanceModel) {
7500                                 distances[candidateId][optionKeys[o]] = d;
7501                             }
7502                         }
7503                         else {
7504                             distances[candidateId][optionKeys[o]] = d;
7505                         }
7506                         //is distance lower?
7507                         if (d < b) {
7508                             b = d; // best (least) distance
7509                             t = i; // unistroke template
7510                         }
7511                         //}
7512                     }
7513                     
7514                 }
7515                 
7516                 var recognitionThreshold = this.useProtractor ? this.protractorRecognitionThreshold : this.dollarOneRecognitionThreshold;
7517                 if (b < recognitionThreshold) {
7518                     // get all gestures with best (least) distance
7519                     var recognizedGestures = {};
7520                     for (var r = 0; r < candidateGestureKeys.length; r++) {
7521                         var options = distances[candidateGestureKeys[r]];
7522                         for (var m = 0; m < Object.keys(options).length; m++) {
7523                             var atomicGestures = options[Object.keys(options)[m]];
7524                             if (atomicGestures == b) {
7525                                 recognizedGestures[candidateGestureKeys[r]] = parseInt(Object.keys(options)[m]);
7526                                 
7527                             }
7528                         }
7529                     }
7530                     return recognizedGestures;
7531                 }
7532                 else {
7533                     return {};
7534                 }
7535                 
7536             },
7537             /**
7538              * Calculate distance between candidate and template based on vectors.
7539              * Protractor algorithm.
7540              * @param {Array} v1 List of template vectors.
7541              * @param {Array} v2 List of candidate vectors.
7542              */
7543             optimalCosineDistance: function(v1, v2){
7544                 var a = 0.0;
7545                 var b = 0.0;
7546                 for (var i = 0; i < v1.length; i += 2) {
7547                     a += v1[i] * v2[i] + v1[i + 1] * v2[i + 1];
7548                     b += v1[i] * v2[i + 1] - v1[i + 1] * v2[i];
7549                 }
7550                 var angle = Math.atan(b / a);
7551                 return Math.acos(a * Math.cos(angle) + b * Math.sin(angle));
7552             },
7553             /**
7554              * Calculate distance between candidate and template based on vectors.
7555              * $1-Algorithm.
7556              * @param {Array} points
7557              * @param {Array} variantPoints
7558              * @param {Number} a
7559              * @param {Number} b
7560              * @param {Number} threshold
7561              */
7562             distanceAtBestAngle: function(points, variantPoints, a, b, threshold){
7563                 var x1 = this.phi * a + (1.0 - this.phi) * b;
7564                 var f1 = this._distanceAtAngle(points, variantPoints, x1);
7565                 var x2 = (1.0 - this.phi) * a + this.phi * b;
7566                 var f2 = this._distanceAtAngle(points, variantPoints, x2);
7567                 while (Math.abs(b - a) > threshold) {
7568                     if (f1 < f2) {
7569                         b = x2;
7570                         x2 = x1;
7571                         f2 = f1;
7572                         x1 = this.phi * a + (1.0 - this.phi) * b;
7573                         f1 = this._distanceAtAngle(points, variantPoints, x1);
7574                     }
7575                     else {
7576                         a = x1;
7577                         x1 = x2;
7578                         f1 = f2;
7579                         x2 = (1.0 - this.phi) * a + this.phi * b;
7580                         f2 = this._distanceAtAngle(points, variantPoints, x2);
7581                     }
7582                 }
7583                 return Math.min(f1, f2);
7584                 
7585             },
7586             /**
7587              * Normalizes templates and returns a list of vectors representing a compareable gesture data structure.
7588              * @param {Object} template
7589              * @param {Boolean} useBoundedRotationInvariance
7590              * @return {Array} List of vectors.
7591              */
7592             getNormalizedVectors: function(template, useBoundedRotationInvariance){
7593                 var points = template.points.slice();
7594                 points = this._resample(points, this.numberOfPoints);
7595                 var radians = this._indicativeAngle(points);
7596                 if (!useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
7597                     points = this._rotateBy(points, -radians);
7598                 }
7599                 points = this._scaleTo(points, this.squareSize, this.oneDThreshold);
7600                 // if (useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
7601                 // this.Points = this._rotateBy(points, +radians); // restore
7602                 // }
7603                 points = this._translateTo(points, this.origin);
7604                 var vectors = this._vectorize(points, useBoundedRotationInvariance);
7605                 return vectors;
7606             },
7607             /**
7608              * Normalizes templates and returns a list of points representing a compareable gesture data structure.
7609              * @param {Object} template
7610              * @param {Boolean} useBoundedRotationInvariance
7611              * @return {Array} Normalized points.
7612              */
7613             getNormalizedPoints: function(template, useBoundedRotationInvariance){
7614             
7615                 var points = template.points.slice();
7616                 points = this._resample(points, this.numberOfPoints);
7617                 var radians = this._indicativeAngle(points);
7618                 if (!useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
7619                     points = this._rotateBy(points, -radians);
7620                 }
7621                 points = this._scaleTo(points, this.squareSize, this.oneDThreshold);
7622                 points = this._translateTo(points, this.origin);
7623                 return points;
7624             },
7625             /**
7626              * Calculate distance at best angle.
7627              * @param {Array} points
7628              * @param {Array} variantPoints
7629              * @param {Number} radians
7630              * @return {Number} Distance
7631              */
7632             _distanceAtAngle: function(points, variantPoints, radians){
7633                 var newpoints = this._rotateBy(points, radians);
7634                 return this._pathDistance(newpoints, variantPoints);
7635             },
7636             /**
7637              * Resample points based on number of points n.
7638              * @param {Array} points
7639              * @param {Number} n
7640              * @param {Array} Resampled points.
7641              */
7642             _resample: function(points, n){
7643             
7644                 var I = this._pathLength(points) / (n - 1); // interval length
7645                 var D = 0.0;
7646                 var newpoints = [points[0]];
7647                 
7648                 for (var i = 1; i < points.length; i++) {
7649                 
7650                     var d = this._distance(points[i - 1], points[i]);
7651                     
7652                     if ((D + d) >= I) {
7653                         var qx = points[i - 1].x +
7654                         ((I - D) / d) *
7655                         (points[i].x - points[i - 1].x);
7656                         
7657                         var qy = points[i - 1].y +
7658                         ((I - D) / d) *
7659                         (points[i].y - points[i - 1].y);
7660                         var q = {
7661                             x: qx,
7662                             y: qy
7663                         };
7664                         newpoints[newpoints.length] = q; // append new point
7665                         // 'q'
7666                         points.splice(i, 0, q); // insert 'q' at position i in
7667                         // points s.t. 'q' will be the next
7668                         // i
7669                         D = 0.0;
7670                         
7671                     }
7672                     else {
7673                         D += d;
7674                     }
7675                 }
7676                 
7677                 // somtimes we fall a rounding-error short of adding the last point, so add it if so
7678                 if (newpoints.length == n - 1) {
7679                     newpoints[newpoints.length] = {
7680                         x: points[points.length - 1].x,
7681                         y: points[points.length - 1].y
7682                     };
7683                 }
7684                 return newpoints;
7685             },
7686             /**
7687              * Calculate indicative angle.
7688              * @param {Array} points
7689              * @return {Number}
7690              */
7691             _indicativeAngle: function(points){
7692                 var c = this._centroid(points);
7693                 return Math.atan2(c.y - points[0].y, c.x - points[0].x);
7694             },
7695             /**
7696              * Rotates points around centroid.
7697              * @param {Array} points
7698              * @param {Number} radians
7699              * @return {Array} Points.
7700              */
7701             _rotateBy: function(points, radians){
7702                 var c = this._centroid(points);
7703                 var cos = Math.cos(radians);
7704                 var sin = Math.sin(radians);
7705                 
7706                 var newpoints = [];
7707                 for (var i = 0; i < points.length; i++) {
7708                     var qx = (points[i].x - c.x) * cos -
7709                     (points[i].y - c.y) *
7710                     sin +
7711                     c.x;
7712                     var qy = (points[i].x - c.x) * sin +
7713                     (points[i].y - c.y) *
7714                     cos +
7715                     c.y;
7716                     newpoints[newpoints.length] = {
7717                         x: qx,
7718                         y: qy
7719                     };
7720                 }
7721                 return newpoints;
7722             },
7723             /**
7724              * Scales bbox uniformly for 1D, non-uniformly for 2D
7725              * @param {Array} points
7726              * @param {Number} size
7727              * @param {Number} oneDratio
7728              * @return {Array} Scaled point path.
7729              */
7730             _scaleTo: function(points, size, oneDratio){
7731                 var B = this._boundingBox(points);
7732                 var uniformly = Math.min(B.width / B.height, B.height / B.width) <=
7733                 oneDratio; // 1D
7734                 // or
7735                 // 2D
7736                 // gesture
7737                 // test
7738                 var newpoints = [];
7739                 for (var i = 0; i < points.length; i++) {
7740                     var qx = (uniformly) ? points[i].x *
7741                     (size / Math.max(B.width, B.height)) : points[i].x * (size / B.width);
7742                     var qy = (uniformly) ? points[i].y *
7743                     (size / Math.max(B.width, B.height)) : points[i].y * (size / B.height);
7744                     newpoints[newpoints.length] = {
7745                         x: qx,
7746                         y: qy
7747                     };
7748                 }
7749                 return newpoints;
7750             },
7751             /**
7752              * Translates points' centroid.
7753              * @param {Array} points
7754              * @param {Object} pt Reference point
7755              * @return {Array} Translated point path.
7756              */
7757             _translateTo: function(points, pt){
7758                 var c = this._centroid(points);
7759                 var newpoints = [];
7760                 for (var i = 0; i < points.length; i++) {
7761                     var qx = points[i].x + pt.x - c.x;
7762                     var qy = points[i].y + pt.y - c.y;
7763                     newpoints[newpoints.length] = {
7764                         x: qx,
7765                         y: qy
7766                     };
7767                 }
7768                 return newpoints;
7769             },
7770             /**
7771              * Calculates path distance based on two points.
7772              * @param {Object} pts1
7773              * @param {Object} pts2
7774              * @return {Number} Distance
7775              */
7776             _pathDistance: function(pts1, pts2){
7777                 var d = 0.0;
7778                 for (var i = 0; i < pts1.length; i++) 
7779                     // assumes pts1.length == pts2.length
7780                     d += this._distance(pts1[i], pts2[i]);
7781                 return d / pts1.length;
7782             },
7783             /**
7784              * Calculates path length.
7785              * @param {Array} points
7786              * @return {Number} Path length.
7787              */
7788             _pathLength: function(points){
7789                 var d = 0.0;
7790                 for (var i = 1; i < points.length; i++) {
7791                     d += this._distance(points[i - 1], points[i]);
7792                 }
7793                 return d;
7794             },
7795             /**
7796              * Calculate centroid.
7797              * @param {Array} points
7798              * @return {Object} Centroid point.
7799              */
7800             _centroid: function(points){
7801                 var x = 0.0, y = 0.0;
7802                 for (var i = 0; i < points.length; i++) {
7803                     x += points[i].x;
7804                     y += points[i].y;
7805                 }
7806                 x /= points.length;
7807                 y /= points.length;
7808                 return {
7809                     x: x,
7810                     y: y
7811                 };
7812             },
7813             /**
7814              * Calculate bounding box of the gesture.
7815              * @param {Array} points
7816              * @return {Object} Bounding box represented by the following parameters: x,y, width and height.
7817              */
7818             _boundingBox: function(points){
7819                 var minX = +Infinity, maxX = -Infinity, minY = +Infinity, maxY = -Infinity;
7820                 for (var i = 0; i < points.length; i++) {
7821                     if (points[i].x < minX) {
7822                         minX = points[i].x;
7823                     }
7824                     if (points[i].x > maxX) {
7825                         maxX = points[i].x;
7826                     }
7827                     if (points[i].y < minY) {
7828                         minY = points[i].y;
7829                     }
7830                     if (points[i].y > maxY) {
7831                         maxY = points[i].y;
7832                     }
7833                 }
7834                 //return new Rectangle(minX, minY, maxX - minX, maxY - minY);
7835                 return {
7836                     x: minX,
7837                     y: minY,
7838                     width: maxX - minX,
7839                     height: maxY - minY
7840                 };
7841             },
7842             /**
7843              * Vectorize gesture path.
7844              * @param {Array} points
7845              * @param {Boolean} useBoundedRotationInvariance
7846              * @return {Array} List of vectors.
7847              */
7848             _vectorize: function(points, useBoundedRotationInvariance){
7849                 /*var cos = 1.0;
7850                  var sin = 0.0;
7851                  if (useBoundedRotationInvariance) {
7852                  var iAngle = Math.atan2(points[0].y, points[0].x);
7853                  var baseOrientation = (Math.PI / 4.0)
7854                  * Math
7855                  .floor((iAngle + Math.PI / 8.0)
7856                  / (Math.PI / 4.0));
7857                  cos = Math.cos(baseOrientation - iAngle);
7858                  sin = Math.sin(baseOrientation - iAngle);
7859                  }*/
7860                 var sum = 0.0;
7861                 var vector = [];
7862                 /*
7863                  * for ( var i = 0; i < points.length; i++) { var newX =
7864                  * points[i].x * cos - points[i].y * sin; var newY = points[i].y *
7865                  * cos + points[i].x * sin; vector[vector.length] = newX;
7866                  * vector[vector.length] = newY; sum += newX * newX + newY *
7867                  * newY; }
7868                  */
7869                 for (var i = 0; i < points.length; i++) {
7870                     vector[vector.length] = points[i].x;
7871                     vector[vector.length] = points[i].y;
7872                     sum += points[i].x * points[i].x +
7873                     points[i].y *
7874                     points[i].y;
7875                 }
7876                 var magnitude = Math.sqrt(sum);
7877                 for (var j = 0; j < vector.length; j++) {
7878                     vector[j] /= magnitude;
7879                 }
7880                 return vector;
7881             },
7882             /**
7883              * Calculate distance between two points.
7884              * @param {Object} p1
7885              * @param {Object} p2
7886              * @return {Number} Distance between points.
7887              */
7888             _distance: function(p1, p2){
7889                 var dx = p2.x - p1.x;
7890                 var dy = p2.y - p1.y;
7891                 return Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
7892             },
7893             /**
7894              * Convert degree to radian.
7895              * @param {Number} d Degrees.
7896              * @return {Number} Radian.
7897              */
7898             _deg2Rad: function(d){
7899                 return (d * Math.PI / 180.0);
7900             },
7901             /**
7902              * Convert radian to degree.
7903              * @param {Number} r Radian.
7904              * @return {Number} Degrees.
7905              */
7906             _rad2Deg: function(r){
7907                 return (r * 180.0 / Math.PI);
7908             }
7909         };
7910         
7911         return {
7912             /**
7913              * Initialize recognizer settings and recognition strategies.
7914              */
7915             init: function(){
7916             
7917                 // init recognition strategies
7918                 this.Strategy.DollarRecognizer = new DollarRecognizer();
7919                 this.Strategy.StaticGestureRecognizer = new StaticGestureRecognizer();
7920                 this.Strategy.RelationRecognizer = new RelationRecognizer();
7921             },
7922             /**
7923              * Possible strategies of gesture recognition.
7924              * a) Strategy.DollarRecognizer
7925              * b) Strategy.StaticGestureRecognizer
7926              * c) Strategy.RelationRecognizer
7927              */
7928             Strategy: {
7929                 DollarRecognizer: null,
7930                 StaticGestureRecognizer: null,
7931                 RelationRecognizer: null
7932             },
7933             /**
7934              * True if the recognizer is busy, else false.
7935              * @type Boolean
7936              * @default false
7937              */
7938             busy: false,
7939             /**
7940              * Start recognizing a gesture with the given recognition context.
7941              * @param {GeForMT.GestureRecognition.RecognitionContext} recognitionContext
7942              */
7943             recognize: function(recognitionContext){
7944             
7945                 this.busy = true;
7946                 
7947                 var atomicPathGestureCandidates = {};
7948                 var atomicStaticGestureCandidates = {};
7949                 
7950                 var priorities = recognitionContext.priorities;
7951                 var gesturePathes = recognitionContext.gesturePathes;
7952                 var gesturePathesHistory = recognitionContext.gesturePathesHistory;
7953                 var onlineRecognition = recognitionContext.online;
7954                 
7955                 for (var i = 0; i < priorities.length; i++) {
7956                     var gestureId = priorities[i];
7957                     var gestureModel = recognitionContext.models[gestureId].model;
7958                     var templates = recognitionContext.gesturePathes[gestureId];
7959                     var checkmodel = recognitionContext.checkmodels[gestureId];
7960                     
7961                     // option checked?
7962                     var options = gestureModel.options;
7963                     for (var j = 0; j < options.length; j++) {
7964                         if (!checkmodel.optionProcessed(j)) {
7965                         
7966                             var composite = options[j].composite;
7967                             if (options[j].isSynchronousComposedGesture ||
7968                             options[j].isAsynchronousComposedGesture) {
7969                                 //synchronous and asynchronous gestures							
7970                                 // atomicPathGestureCandidates[gestureId][j] =
7971                                 // composite;
7972                                 // get expected number of contacts and check for
7973                                 // path or static
7974                                 var numberOfContacts = 0;
7975                                 var allPathGestures = true;
7976                                 for (var at = 0; at < composite.length; at++) {
7977                                     if (composite[at].numberOfContacts == null) {
7978                                         numberOfContacts = null;
7979                                         break;
7980                                     }
7981                                     else {
7982                                         numberOfContacts = numberOfContacts +
7983                                         composite[at].numberOfContacts;
7984                                     }
7985                                     if (!composite[at].isPathGesture &&
7986                                     !allPathGestures) {
7987                                         allPathGestures = false;
7988                                     }
7989                                 }
7990                                 
7991                                 // check number of contacts
7992                                 if (numberOfContacts == null ||
7993                                 numberOfContacts == templates.length) {
7994                                 
7995                                     if (allPathGestures) {
7996                                         //atomic gesture is path
7997                                         if (typeof atomicPathGestureCandidates[gestureId] == 'undefined') {
7998                                             atomicPathGestureCandidates[gestureId] = {};
7999                                         }
8000                                         atomicPathGestureCandidates[gestureId][j] = composite;
8001                                     }
8002                                     else {
8003                                         //atomic gestures are static
8004                                         if (typeof atomicStaticGestureCandidates[gestureId] == 'undefined') {
8005                                             atomicStaticGestureCandidates[gestureId] = {};
8006                                         }
8007                                         atomicStaticGestureCandidates[gestureId][j] = composite;
8008                                     }
8009                                 }
8010                             }
8011                             else {
8012                                 // unistroke gesture (can also be a part of multistroke gesture)
8013                                 var compTaskIdx = checkmodel.getNextTaskIdx(j);
8014                                 var atom = composite[compTaskIdx];
8015                                 // check number of contacts
8016                                 if (atom.numberOfContacts == null ||
8017                                 atom.numberOfContacts == templates.length) {
8018                                     if (atom.isPathGesture) {
8019                                         //atomic gesture is path
8020                                         if (typeof atomicPathGestureCandidates[gestureId] == 'undefined') {
8021                                             atomicPathGestureCandidates[gestureId] = {};
8022                                         }
8023                                         atomicPathGestureCandidates[gestureId][j] = [atom];
8024                                         
8025                                     }
8026                                     else {
8027                                         //atomic gesture is static
8028                                         if (typeof atomicStaticGestureCandidates[gestureId] == 'undefined') {
8029                                             atomicStaticGestureCandidates[gestureId] = {};
8030                                         }
8031                                         atomicStaticGestureCandidates[gestureId][j] = [atom];
8032                                     }
8033                                 }
8034                                 
8035                             }
8036                             
8037                         }
8038                     }
8039                 }
8040                 
8041                 var offlineRecognizerResult = {};
8042                 var staticRecognizerResult = {};
8043                 var recognitionResult = {};
8044                 
8045                 // recognize offline path gestures
8046                 if (Object.keys(atomicPathGestureCandidates).length > 0) {
8047                     offlineRecognizerResult = this.Strategy.DollarRecognizer.recognize(gesturePathes, atomicPathGestureCandidates);
8048                 }
8049 
8050                 //recognize point gestures
8051                 if (Object.keys(atomicStaticGestureCandidates).length > 0) {
8052                     staticRecognizerResult = this.Strategy.StaticGestureRecognizer.recognize(gesturePathes, atomicStaticGestureCandidates);
8053                 }
8054                 
8055                 if (Object.keys(offlineRecognizerResult).length > 0) {
8056                     recognitionResult = offlineRecognizerResult;
8057                 }
8058                 else 
8059                     if (Object.keys(staticRecognizerResult).length > 0) {
8060                         recognitionResult = staticRecognizerResult;
8061                     }
8062 
8063                 var recognitionResultKeys = Object.keys(recognitionResult);
8064                 // check relation properties
8065                 if (recognitionResultKeys.length > 0) {
8066                     var relationCheckContext = {};
8067                     var newRecognitionResult = {};
8068                     
8069                     for (var r = 0; r < recognitionResultKeys.length; r++) {
8070                         var id = recognitionResultKeys[r];
8071                         var model = recognitionContext.models[id].model;
8072                         var option = model.options[recognitionResult[id]];
8073                         var relation = option.relationType;
8074                         if (relation !== null) {
8075                             relationCheckContext[id] = {
8076                                 option: recognitionResult[id],
8077                                 relation: relation,
8078                                 isMultistroke: option.isMultistrokeGesture,
8079                                 isMultitouch: option.isSynchronousComposedGesture || option.isAsynchronousComposedGesture || option.composite[0].numberOfContacts !== 1
8080                             };
8081                         }
8082                         else {
8083                             newRecognitionResult[id] = recognitionResult[id];
8084                         }
8085                         
8086                     }
8087                     
8088                     var relationCheckResult = {};
8089                     if (Object.keys(relationCheckContext).length > 0) {
8090                         //check relations
8091                         relationCheckResult = this.Strategy.RelationRecognizer.recognize(gesturePathes, gesturePathesHistory, relationCheckContext);
8092                         
8093                     }
8094                     var relationCheckResultKeys = Object.keys(relationCheckResult);
8095                     
8096                     // add recognizedRelations of checkResult
8097                     for (var rc = 0; rc < relationCheckResultKeys.length; rc++) {
8098                         newRecognitionResult[relationCheckResultKeys[rc]] = relationCheckResult[relationCheckResultKeys[rc]];
8099                     }
8100                     recognitionResult = newRecognitionResult;
8101                 }
8102                 if (!onlineRecognition) {
8103                     // update checklists
8104                     var recognitionResultKeys = Object.keys(recognitionResult);
8105                     for (var r = 0; r < recognitionResultKeys.length; r++) {
8106                         var gestureId = recognitionResultKeys[r];
8107                         var optionId = recognitionResult[gestureId];
8108                         var option = recognitionContext.models[gestureId].model.options[optionId];
8109                         if (option.isSynchronousComposedGesture ||
8110                         option.isAsynchronousComposedGesture) {
8111                             recognitionContext.checkmodels[gestureId].setOtherOptionsToFalse(optionId);
8112                             recognitionContext.checkmodels[gestureId].setAllAtomsOfOptionTrue(optionId);
8113                         }
8114                         else {
8115                             var taskIdx = recognitionContext.checkmodels[gestureId].getNextTaskIdx(optionId);
8116                             recognitionContext.checkmodels[gestureId].setOtherOptionsToFalse(optionId);
8117                             recognitionContext.checkmodels[gestureId].checkmodel[optionId][taskIdx] = true;
8118                         }
8119                     }
8120                 }
8121                 // call process manager back
8122                 recognitionContext.recognizedGestures = recognitionResult;
8123                 recognitionContext.recognitionCallback(recognitionContext);
8124                 
8125                 this.busy = false;
8126             }
8127         };
8128     })();

8130     /**
8131      * A task is managed by RecognitionTaskManager. The task object bundles the
8132      * formal criteria of a gesture and recognized events, that must be
8133      * compared.

8135      * @param {Object} eventProfiles
8136      * @param {Object} eventProfilesHistory
8137      * @param {Object} gesturePathes
8138      * @param {Object} gesturePathesHistory
8139      * @param {Object} models
8140      * @param {Object} checkmodels
8141      * @param {Function} recognitionCallback
8142      * @param {Boolean} online
8143      */
8144     function RecognitionContext(priorities, eventProfiles, eventProfilesHistory, gesturePathes, gesturePathesHistory, models, checkmodels, recognitionCallback, online){
8145         this.priorities = priorities;
8146         this.eventProfiles = eventProfiles;
8147         this.gesturePathes = gesturePathes;
8148         this.eventProfilesHistory = eventProfilesHistory;

8150         this.models = models;
8151         this.recognizedGestures = {};
8152         this.checkmodels = checkmodels;
8153         this.recognitionCallback = recognitionCallback;
8154         if (typeof online !== 'undefined') {
8155             this.online = online;
8156         }
8157     }

8225     /**
8226      * Represents a checklist according to the options and composite items of
8227      * the gesture model.
8228      * @param {GeForMT.GestureModel.GestureObjectModel}
8229      *            model
8230      *  @class
8231      */
8232     function CheckModel(model){
8233         var checklists = [];
8234         for (var o = 0; o < model.options.length; o++) {
8235             var option = model.options[o];
8236             var compositeChecklist = [];
8237             for (var a = 0; a < option.composite.length; a++) {
8238                 var gestureAtom = option.composite[a];
8239                 compositeChecklist.push(null);
8240             }
8241             checklists.push(compositeChecklist);
8242         }
8243         this.checkmodel = checklists;
8244     }
8245     
8246     CheckModel.prototype = /*@lends*/ {
8247         /**
8248          * Checkmodel representing checklists for options and atomic gestures.
8249          * Is generated based on the gesture model.
8250          * @type Array
8251          * @default null.
8252          */
8253         checkmodel: null,
8254         /**
8255          * Option at position idx processed? Items can be true or false
8256          * @param {Object} idx
8257          * @return Returns false, if the option contains null values.
8258          */
8259         optionProcessed: function(idx){
8260             var option = this.checkmodel[idx];
8261             for (var i = 0; i < option.length; i++) {
8262                 var atom = option[i];
8263                 if (atom === null) {
8264                     return false;
8265                 }
8266             }
8267             return true;
8268         },
8269         /**
8270          * Returns the index of the next task for recongizer based on the given option index.
8271          * @param {Object} optionIdx
8272          */
8273         getNextTaskIdx: function(optionIdx){
8274             var option = this.checkmodel[optionIdx];
8275             var taskIdx = 0;
8276             for (var i = 0; i < option.length; i++) {
8277                 var atom = option[i];
8278                 if (atom !== null) {
8279                     taskIdx++;
8280                 }
8281                 else {
8282                     break;
8283                 }
8284             }
8285             
8286             return taskIdx;
8287         },
8288         /**
8289          * Returns true, if all atomic gestures and options has been recognized successfully (all check items true?).
8290          * @return Boolean
8291          */
8292         processedSuccessfully: function(){
8293             var check = true;
8294             for (var i = 0; i < this.checkmodel.length; i++) {
8295                 var composite = this.checkmodel[i];
8296                 for (var j = 0; j < composite.length; j++) {
8297                     var atom = composite[j];
8298                     if (atom === null) {
8299                         return false;
8300                     }
8301                     else 
8302                         if (!atom) {
8303                             return false;
8304                         }
8305                 }
8306             }
8307             return true;
8308         },
8309         /**
8310          * Returns true, if all atomic gestures of one option has been recognized successfully (all check items of option true?).
8311          * @return Boolean
8312          */
8313         oneOptionProcessedSuccessfully: function(){
8314             for (var i = 0; i < this.checkmodel.length; i++) {
8315                 var option = this.checkmodel[i];
8316                 var optionProcessedSuc = false;
8317                 for (var j = 0; j < option.length; j++) {
8318                     var atom = option[j];
8319                     if (atom === null) {
8320                         optionProcessedSuc = false;
8321                         break;
8322                     }
8323                     else 
8324                         if (!atom) {
8325                             optionProcessedSuc = false;
8326                             break;
8327                         }
8328                         else 
8329                             if (atom) {
8330                                 optionProcessedSuc = true;
8331                             }
8332                 }
8333                 
8334                 if (optionProcessedSuc) {
8335                     return true;
8336                 }
8337             }
8338             return false;
8339         },
8340         /**
8341          * Set all values of all options except the option at the given position to false.
8342          * @param {Object} optionIdx
8343          */
8344         setOtherOptionsToFalse: function(optionIdx){
8345             for (var i = 0; i < this.checkmodel.length; i++) {
8346                 var option = this.checkmodel[i];
8347                 if (i !== optionIdx) {
8348                     for (var j = 0; j < option.length; j++) {
8349                         option[j] = false;
8350                         
8351                     }
8352                 }
8353             }
8354         },
8355         /**
8356          * Set status 'recognized' on all atomic gesture of a specific option.
8357          * @param {Number} optionIdx
8358          */
8359         setAllAtomsOfOptionTrue: function(optionIdx){
8360             var option = this.checkmodel[optionIdx];
8361             for (var a = 0; a < option.length; a++) {
8362                 option[a] = true;
8363             }
8364         }
8365     };

8435         removeGestureRecognitionEventListener: function(eventName, callback){

8440                         list.splice(i, 1);

8448 /*!
8449  * Sizzle CSS Selector Engine
8450  *  Copyright 2011, The Dojo Foundation
8451  *  Released under the MIT, BSD, and GPL Licenses.
8452  *  More information: http://sizzlejs.com/
8453  */
8454 (function(){
8455 
8456 var chunker = /((?:\((?:\([^()]+\)|[^()]+)+\)|\[(?:\[[^\[\]]*\]|['"][^'"]*['"]|[^\[\]'"]+)+\]|\\.|[^ >+~,(\[\\]+)+|[>+~])(\s*,\s*)?((?:.|\r|\n)*)/g,
8457 	done = 0,
8458 	toString = Object.prototype.toString,
8459 	hasDuplicate = false,
8460 	baseHasDuplicate = true,
8461 	rBackslash = /\\/g,
8462 	rNonWord = /\W/;
8463 
8464 // Here we check if the JavaScript engine is using some sort of
8465 // optimization where it does not always call our comparision
8466 // function. If that is the case, discard the hasDuplicate value.
8467 //   Thus far that includes Google Chrome.
8468 [0, 0].sort(function() {
8469 	baseHasDuplicate = false;
8470 	return 0;
8471 });
8472 
8473 var Sizzle = function( selector, context, results, seed ) {
8474 	results = results || [];
8475 	context = context || document;
8476 
8477 	var origContext = context;
8478 
8479 	if ( context.nodeType !== 1 && context.nodeType !== 9 ) {
8480 		return [];
8481 	}
8482 	
8483 	if ( !selector || typeof selector !== "string" ) {
8484 		return results;
8485 	}
8486 
8487 	var m, set, checkSet, extra, ret, cur, pop, i,
8488 		prune = true,
8489 		contextXML = Sizzle.isXML( context ),
8490 		parts = [],
8491 		soFar = selector;
8492 	
8493 	// Reset the position of the chunker regexp (start from head)
8494 	do {
8495 		chunker.exec( "" );
8496 		m = chunker.exec( soFar );
8497 
8498 		if ( m ) {
8499 			soFar = m[3];
8500 		
8501 			parts.push( m[1] );
8502 		
8503 			if ( m[2] ) {
8504 				extra = m[3];
8505 				break;
8506 			}
8507 		}
8508 	} while ( m );
8509 
8510 	if ( parts.length > 1 && origPOS.exec( selector ) ) {
8511 
8512 		if ( parts.length === 2 && Expr.relative[ parts[0] ] ) {
8513 			set = posProcess( parts[0] + parts[1], context );
8514 
8515 		} else {
8516 			set = Expr.relative[ parts[0] ] ?
8517 				[ context ] :
8518 				Sizzle( parts.shift(), context );
8519 
8520 			while ( parts.length ) {
8521 				selector = parts.shift();
8522 
8523 				if ( Expr.relative[ selector ] ) {
8524 					selector += parts.shift();
8525 				}
8526 				
8527 				set = posProcess( selector, set );
8528 			}
8529 		}
8530 
8531 	} else {
8532 		// Take a shortcut and set the context if the root selector is an ID
8533 		// (but not if it'll be faster if the inner selector is an ID)
8534 		if ( !seed && parts.length > 1 && context.nodeType === 9 && !contextXML &&
8535 				Expr.match.ID.test(parts[0]) && !Expr.match.ID.test(parts[parts.length - 1]) ) {
8536 
8537 			ret = Sizzle.find( parts.shift(), context, contextXML );
8538 			context = ret.expr ?
8539 				Sizzle.filter( ret.expr, ret.set )[0] :
8540 				ret.set[0];
8541 		}
8542 
8543 		if ( context ) {
8544 			ret = seed ?
8545 				{ expr: parts.pop(), set: makeArray(seed) } :
8546 				Sizzle.find( parts.pop(), parts.length === 1 && (parts[0] === "~" || parts[0] === "+") && context.parentNode ? context.parentNode : context, contextXML );
8547 
8548 			set = ret.expr ?
8549 				Sizzle.filter( ret.expr, ret.set ) :
8550 				ret.set;
8551 
8552 			if ( parts.length > 0 ) {
8553 				checkSet = makeArray( set );
8554 
8555 			} else {
8556 				prune = false;
8557 			}
8558 
8559 			while ( parts.length ) {
8560 				cur = parts.pop();
8561 				pop = cur;
8562 
8563 				if ( !Expr.relative[ cur ] ) {
8564 					cur = "";
8565 				} else {
8566 					pop = parts.pop();
8567 				}
8568 
8569 				if ( pop == null ) {
8570 					pop = context;
8571 				}
8572 
8573 				Expr.relative[ cur ]( checkSet, pop, contextXML );
8574 			}
8575 
8576 		} else {
8577 			checkSet = parts = [];
8578 		}
8579 	}
8580 
8581 	if ( !checkSet ) {
8582 		checkSet = set;
8583 	}
8584 
8585 	if ( !checkSet ) {
8586 		Sizzle.error( cur || selector );
8587 	}
8588 
8589 	if ( toString.call(checkSet) === "[object Array]" ) {
8590 		if ( !prune ) {
8591 			results.push.apply( results, checkSet );
8592 
8593 		} else if ( context && context.nodeType === 1 ) {
8594 			for ( i = 0; checkSet[i] != null; i++ ) {
8595 				if ( checkSet[i] && (checkSet[i] === true || checkSet[i].nodeType === 1 && Sizzle.contains(context, checkSet[i])) ) {
8596 					results.push( set[i] );
8597 				}
8598 			}
8599 
8600 		} else {
8601 			for ( i = 0; checkSet[i] != null; i++ ) {
8602 				if ( checkSet[i] && checkSet[i].nodeType === 1 ) {
8603 					results.push( set[i] );
8604 				}
8605 			}
8606 		}
8607 
8608 	} else {
8609 		makeArray( checkSet, results );
8610 	}
8611 
8612 	if ( extra ) {
8613 		Sizzle( extra, origContext, results, seed );
8614 		Sizzle.uniqueSort( results );
8615 	}
8616 
8617 	return results;
8618 };
8619 
8620 Sizzle.uniqueSort = function( results ) {
8621 	if ( sortOrder ) {
8622 		hasDuplicate = baseHasDuplicate;
8623 		results.sort( sortOrder );
8624 
8625 		if ( hasDuplicate ) {
8626 			for ( var i = 1; i < results.length; i++ ) {
8627 				if ( results[i] === results[ i - 1 ] ) {
8628 					results.splice( i--, 1 );
8629 				}
8630 			}
8631 		}
8632 	}
8633 
8634 	return results;
8635 };
8636 
8637 Sizzle.matches = function( expr, set ) {
8638 	return Sizzle( expr, null, null, set );
8639 };
8640 
8641 Sizzle.matchesSelector = function( node, expr ) {
8642 	return Sizzle( expr, null, null, [node] ).length > 0;
8643 };
8644 
8645 Sizzle.find = function( expr, context, isXML ) {
8646 	var set;
8647 
8648 	if ( !expr ) {
8649 		return [];
8650 	}
8651 
8652 	for ( var i = 0, l = Expr.order.length; i < l; i++ ) {
8653 		var match,
8654 			type = Expr.order[i];
8655 		
8656 		if ( (match = Expr.leftMatch[ type ].exec( expr )) ) {
8657 			var left = match[1];
8658 			match.splice( 1, 1 );
8659 
8660 			if ( left.substr( left.length - 1 ) !== "\\" ) {
8661 				match[1] = (match[1] || "").replace( rBackslash, "" );
8662 				set = Expr.find[ type ]( match, context, isXML );
8663 
8664 				if ( set != null ) {
8665 					expr = expr.replace( Expr.match[ type ], "" );
8666 					break;
8667 				}
8668 			}
8669 		}
8670 	}
8671 
8672 	if ( !set ) {
8673 		set = typeof context.getElementsByTagName !== "undefined" ?
8674 			context.getElementsByTagName( "*" ) :
8675 			[];
8676 	}
8677 
8678 	return { set: set, expr: expr };
8679 };
8680 
8681 Sizzle.filter = function( expr, set, inplace, not ) {
8682 	var match, anyFound,
8683 		old = expr,
8684 		result = [],
8685 		curLoop = set,
8686 		isXMLFilter = set && set[0] && Sizzle.isXML( set[0] );
8687 
8688 	while ( expr && set.length ) {
8689 		for ( var type in Expr.filter ) {
8690 			if ( (match = Expr.leftMatch[ type ].exec( expr )) != null && match[2] ) {
8691 				var found, item,
8692 					filter = Expr.filter[ type ],
8693 					left = match[1];
8694 
8695 				anyFound = false;
8696 
8697 				match.splice(1,1);
8698 
8699 				if ( left.substr( left.length - 1 ) === "\\" ) {
8700 					continue;
8701 				}
8702 
8703 				if ( curLoop === result ) {
8704 					result = [];
8705 				}
8706 
8707 				if ( Expr.preFilter[ type ] ) {
8708 					match = Expr.preFilter[ type ]( match, curLoop, inplace, result, not, isXMLFilter );
8709 
8710 					if ( !match ) {
8711 						anyFound = found = true;
8712 
8713 					} else if ( match === true ) {
8714 						continue;
8715 					}
8716 				}
8717 
8718 				if ( match ) {
8719 					for ( var i = 0; (item = curLoop[i]) != null; i++ ) {
8720 						if ( item ) {
8721 							found = filter( item, match, i, curLoop );
8722 							var pass = not ^ !!found;
8723 
8724 							if ( inplace && found != null ) {
8725 								if ( pass ) {
8726 									anyFound = true;
8727 
8728 								} else {
8729 									curLoop[i] = false;
8730 								}
8731 
8732 							} else if ( pass ) {
8733 								result.push( item );
8734 								anyFound = true;
8735 							}
8736 						}
8737 					}
8738 				}
8739 
8740 				if ( found !== undefined ) {
8741 					if ( !inplace ) {
8742 						curLoop = result;
8743 					}
8744 
8745 					expr = expr.replace( Expr.match[ type ], "" );
8746 
8747 					if ( !anyFound ) {
8748 						return [];
8749 					}
8750 
8751 					break;
8752 				}
8753 			}
8754 		}
8755 
8756 		// Improper expression
8757 		if ( expr === old ) {
8758 			if ( anyFound == null ) {
8759 				Sizzle.error( expr );
8760 
8761 			} else {
8762 				break;
8763 			}
8764 		}
8765 
8766 		old = expr;
8767 	}
8768 
8769 	return curLoop;
8770 };
8771 
8772 Sizzle.error = function( msg ) {
8773 	throw "Syntax error, unrecognized expression: " + msg;
8774 };

9019 				return true;
9020 			}

9155 		PSEUDO: function( elem, match, i, array ) {
9156 			var name = match[1],
9157 				filter = Expr.filters[ name ];
9158 
9159 			if ( filter ) {
9160 				return filter( elem, i, match, array );
9161 
9162 			} else if ( name === "contains" ) {
9163 				return (elem.textContent || elem.innerText || Sizzle.getText([ elem ]) || "").indexOf(match[3]) >= 0;
9164 
9165 			} else if ( name === "not" ) {
9166 				var not = match[3];
9167 
9168 				for ( var j = 0, l = not.length; j < l; j++ ) {
9169 					if ( not[j] === elem ) {
9170 						return false;

9172 				}
9173 
9174 				return true;
9175 
9176 			} else {
9177 				Sizzle.error( name );

9179 		},
9180 
9181 		CHILD: function( elem, match ) {
9182 			var type = match[1],
9183 				node = elem;
9184 
9185 			switch ( type ) {
9186 				case "only":
9187 				case "first":
9188 					while ( (node = node.previousSibling) )	 {
9189 						if ( node.nodeType === 1 ) { 
9190 							return false; 
9191 						}
9192 					}
9193 
9194 					if ( type === "first" ) { 
9195 						return true; 
9196 					}
9197 
9198 					node = elem;
9199 
9200 				case "last":
9201 					while ( (node = node.nextSibling) )	 {
9202 						if ( node.nodeType === 1 ) { 
9203 							return false; 
9204 						}
9205 					}
9206 
9207 					return true;
9208 
9209 				case "nth":
9210 					var first = match[2],
9211 						last = match[3];
9212 
9213 					if ( first === 1 && last === 0 ) {
9214 						return true;
9215 					}
9216 					
9217 					var doneName = match[0],
9218 						parent = elem.parentNode;
9219 	
9220 					if ( parent && (parent.sizcache !== doneName || !elem.nodeIndex) ) {
9221 						var count = 0;
9222 						
9223 						for ( node = parent.firstChild; node; node = node.nextSibling ) {
9224 							if ( node.nodeType === 1 ) {
9225 								node.nodeIndex = ++count;
9226 							}
9227 						} 
9228 
9229 						parent.sizcache = doneName;
9230 					}
9231 					
9232 					var diff = elem.nodeIndex - last;
9233 
9234 					if ( first === 0 ) {
9235 						return diff === 0;
9236 
9237 					} else {
9238 						return ( diff % first === 0 && diff / first >= 0 );
9239 					}
9240 			}
9241 		},
9242 
9243 		ID: function( elem, match ) {
9244 			return elem.nodeType === 1 && elem.getAttribute("id") === match;
9245 		},
9246 
9247 		TAG: function( elem, match ) {
9248 			return (match === "*" && elem.nodeType === 1) || elem.nodeName.toLowerCase() === match;
9249 		},
9250 		
9251 		CLASS: function( elem, match ) {
9252 			return (" " + (elem.className || elem.getAttribute("class")) + " ")
9253 				.indexOf( match ) > -1;
9254 		},
9255 
9256 		ATTR: function( elem, match ) {
9257 			var name = match[1],
9258 				result = Expr.attrHandle[ name ] ?
9259 					Expr.attrHandle[ name ]( elem ) :
9260 					elem[ name ] != null ?
9261 						elem[ name ] :
9262 						elem.getAttribute( name ),
9263 				value = result + "",
9264 				type = match[2],
9265 				check = match[4];
9266 
9267 			return result == null ?
9268 				type === "!=" :
9269 				type === "=" ?
9270 				value === check :
9271 				type === "*=" ?
9272 				value.indexOf(check) >= 0 :
9273 				type === "~=" ?
9274 				(" " + value + " ").indexOf(check) >= 0 :
9275 				!check ?
9276 				value && result !== false :
9277 				type === "!=" ?
9278 				value !== check :
9279 				type === "^=" ?
9280 				value.indexOf(check) === 0 :
9281 				type === "$=" ?
9282 				value.substr(value.length - check.length) === check :
9283 				type === "|=" ?
9284 				value === check || value.substr(0, check.length + 1) === check + "-" :
9285 				false;
9286 		},
9287 
9288 		POS: function( elem, match, i, array ) {
9289 			var name = match[2],
9290 				filter = Expr.setFilters[ name ];
9291 
9292 			if ( filter ) {
9293 				return filter( elem, i, match, array );
9294 			}
9295 		}
9296 	}
9297 };

9309 var makeArray = function( array, results ) {
9310 	array = Array.prototype.slice.call( array, 0 );
9311 
9312 	if ( results ) {
9313 		results.push.apply( results, array );
9314 		return results;
9315 	}
9316 	
9317 	return array;

9320 // Perform a simple check to determine if the browser is capable of
9321 // converting a NodeList to an array using builtin methods.
9322 // Also verifies that the returned array holds DOM nodes
9323 // (which is not the case in the Blackberry browser)
9324 try {
9325 	Array.prototype.slice.call( document.documentElement.childNodes, 0 )[0].nodeType;
9326 
9327 // Provide a fallback method if it does not work
9328 } catch( e ) {
9329 	makeArray = function( array, results ) {
9330 		var i = 0,
9331 			ret = results || [];
9332 
9333 		if ( toString.call(array) === "[object Array]" ) {
9334 			Array.prototype.push.apply( ret, array );
9335 
9336 		} else {
9337 			if ( typeof array.length === "number" ) {
9338 				for ( var l = array.length; i < l; i++ ) {
9339 					ret.push( array[i] );
9340 				}
9341 
9342 			} else {
9343 				for ( ; array[i]; i++ ) {
9344 					ret.push( array[i] );
9345 				}
9346 			}
9347 		}
9348 
9349 		return ret;
9350 	};
9351 }

9353 var sortOrder, siblingCheck;
9354 
9355 if ( document.documentElement.compareDocumentPosition ) {
9356 	sortOrder = function( a, b ) {
9357 		if ( a === b ) {
9358 			hasDuplicate = true;
9359 			return 0;
9360 		}
9361 
9362 		if ( !a.compareDocumentPosition || !b.compareDocumentPosition ) {
9363 			return a.compareDocumentPosition ? -1 : 1;
9364 		}
9365 
9366 		return a.compareDocumentPosition(b) & 4 ? -1 : 1;
9367 	};
9368 
9369 } else {
9370 	sortOrder = function( a, b ) {
9371 		// The nodes are identical, we can exit early
9372 		if ( a === b ) {
9373 			hasDuplicate = true;
9374 			return 0;
9375 
9376 		// Fallback to using sourceIndex (in IE) if it's available on both nodes
9377 		} else if ( a.sourceIndex && b.sourceIndex ) {
9378 			return a.sourceIndex - b.sourceIndex;
9379 		}
9380 
9381 		var al, bl,
9382 			ap = [],
9383 			bp = [],
9384 			aup = a.parentNode,
9385 			bup = b.parentNode,
9386 			cur = aup;
9387 
9388 		// If the nodes are siblings (or identical) we can do a quick check
9389 		if ( aup === bup ) {
9390 			return siblingCheck( a, b );
9391 
9392 		// If no parents were found then the nodes are disconnected
9393 		} else if ( !aup ) {
9394 			return -1;
9395 
9396 		} else if ( !bup ) {
9397 			return 1;
9398 		}
9399 
9400 		// Otherwise they're somewhere else in the tree so we need
9401 		// to build up a full list of the parentNodes for comparison
9402 		while ( cur ) {
9403 			ap.unshift( cur );
9404 			cur = cur.parentNode;
9405 		}
9406 
9407 		cur = bup;
9408 
9409 		while ( cur ) {
9410 			bp.unshift( cur );
9411 			cur = cur.parentNode;
9412 		}
9413 
9414 		al = ap.length;
9415 		bl = bp.length;
9416 
9417 		// Start walking down the tree looking for a discrepancy
9418 		for ( var i = 0; i < al && i < bl; i++ ) {
9419 			if ( ap[i] !== bp[i] ) {
9420 				return siblingCheck( ap[i], bp[i] );
9421 			}
9422 		}
9423 
9424 		// We ended someplace up the tree so do a sibling check
9425 		return i === al ?
9426 			siblingCheck( a, bp[i], -1 ) :
9427 			siblingCheck( ap[i], b, 1 );
9428 	};
9429 
9430 	siblingCheck = function( a, b, ret ) {
9431 		if ( a === b ) {
9432 			return ret;
9433 		}
9434 
9435 		var cur = a.nextSibling;
9436 
9437 		while ( cur ) {
9438 			if ( cur === b ) {
9439 				return -1;
9440 			}
9441 
9442 			cur = cur.nextSibling;
9443 		}
9444 
9445 		return 1;
9446 	};
9447 }
9448 
9449 // Utility function for retreiving the text value of an array of DOM nodes
9450 Sizzle.getText = function( elems ) {
9451 	var ret = "", elem;
9452 
9453 	for ( var i = 0; elems[i]; i++ ) {
9454 		elem = elems[i];
9455 
9456 		// Get the text from text nodes and CDATA nodes
9457 		if ( elem.nodeType === 3 || elem.nodeType === 4 ) {
9458 			ret += elem.nodeValue;
9459 
9460 		// Traverse everything else, except comment nodes
9461 		} else if ( elem.nodeType !== 8 ) {
9462 			ret += Sizzle.getText( elem.childNodes );
9463 		}
9464 	}
9465 
9466 	return ret;
9467 };

9555 if ( document.querySelectorAll ) {
9556 	(function(){
9557 		var oldSizzle = Sizzle,
9558 			div = document.createElement("div"),
9559 			id = "__sizzle__";
9560 
9561 		div.innerHTML = "<p class='TEST'></p>";
9562 
9563 		// Safari can't handle uppercase or unicode characters when
9564 		// in quirks mode.
9565 		if ( div.querySelectorAll && div.querySelectorAll(".TEST").length === 0 ) {
9566 			return;
9567 		}
9568 	
9569 		Sizzle = function( query, context, extra, seed ) {
9570 			context = context || document;
9571 
9572 			// Only use querySelectorAll on non-XML documents
9573 			// (ID selectors don't work in non-HTML documents)
9574 			if ( !seed && !Sizzle.isXML(context) ) {
9575 				// See if we find a selector to speed up
9576 				var match = /^(\w+$)|^\.([\w\-]+$)|^#([\w\-]+$)/.exec( query );
9577 				
9578 				if ( match && (context.nodeType === 1 || context.nodeType === 9) ) {
9579 					// Speed-up: Sizzle("TAG")
9580 					if ( match[1] ) {
9581 						return makeArray( context.getElementsByTagName( query ), extra );
9582 					
9583 					// Speed-up: Sizzle(".CLASS")
9584 					} else if ( match[2] && Expr.find.CLASS && context.getElementsByClassName ) {
9585 						return makeArray( context.getElementsByClassName( match[2] ), extra );
9586 					}
9587 				}
9588 				
9589 				if ( context.nodeType === 9 ) {
9590 					// Speed-up: Sizzle("body")
9591 					// The body element only exists once, optimize finding it
9592 					if ( query === "body" && context.body ) {
9593 						return makeArray( [ context.body ], extra );
9594 						
9595 					// Speed-up: Sizzle("#ID")
9596 					} else if ( match && match[3] ) {
9597 						var elem = context.getElementById( match[3] );
9598 
9599 						// Check parentNode to catch when Blackberry 4.6 returns
9600 						// nodes that are no longer in the document #6963
9601 						if ( elem && elem.parentNode ) {
9602 							// Handle the case where IE and Opera return items
9603 							// by name instead of ID
9604 							if ( elem.id === match[3] ) {
9605 								return makeArray( [ elem ], extra );
9606 							}
9607 							
9608 						} else {
9609 							return makeArray( [], extra );
9610 						}
9611 					}
9612 					
9613 					try {
9614 						return makeArray( context.querySelectorAll(query), extra );
9615 					} catch(qsaError) {}
9616 
9617 				// qSA works strangely on Element-rooted queries
9618 				// We can work around this by specifying an extra ID on the root
9619 				// and working up from there (Thanks to Andrew Dupont for the technique)
9620 				// IE 8 doesn't work on object elements
9621 				} else if ( context.nodeType === 1 && context.nodeName.toLowerCase() !== "object" ) {
9622 					var oldContext = context,
9623 						old = context.getAttribute( "id" ),
9624 						nid = old || id,
9625 						hasParent = context.parentNode,
9626 						relativeHierarchySelector = /^\s*[+~]/.test( query );
9627 
9628 					if ( !old ) {
9629 						context.setAttribute( "id", nid );
9630 					} else {
9631 						nid = nid.replace( /'/g, "\\$&" );
9632 					}
9633 					if ( relativeHierarchySelector && hasParent ) {
9634 						context = context.parentNode;
9635 					}
9636 
9637 					try {
9638 						if ( !relativeHierarchySelector || hasParent ) {
9639 							return makeArray( context.querySelectorAll( "[id='" + nid + "'] " + query ), extra );
9640 						}
9641 
9642 					} catch(pseudoError) {
9643 					} finally {
9644 						if ( !old ) {
9645 							oldContext.removeAttribute( "id" );
9646 						}
9647 					}
9648 				}
9649 			}
9650 		
9651 			return oldSizzle(query, context, extra, seed);
9652 		};
9653 
9654 		for ( var prop in oldSizzle ) {
9655 			Sizzle[ prop ] = oldSizzle[ prop ];
9656 		}
9657 
9658 		// release memory in IE
9659 		div = null;
9660 	})();
9661 }

9736 function dirNodeCheck( dir, cur, doneName, checkSet, nodeCheck, isXML ) {
9737 	for ( var i = 0, l = checkSet.length; i < l; i++ ) {
9738 		var elem = checkSet[i];
9739 
9740 		if ( elem ) {
9741 			var match = false;
9742 
9743 			elem = elem[dir];
9744 
9745 			while ( elem ) {
9746 				if ( elem.sizcache === doneName ) {
9747 					match = checkSet[elem.sizset];
9748 					break;
9749 				}
9750 
9751 				if ( elem.nodeType === 1 && !isXML ){
9752 					elem.sizcache = doneName;
9753 					elem.sizset = i;
9754 				}
9755 
9756 				if ( elem.nodeName.toLowerCase() === cur ) {
9757 					match = elem;
9758 					break;
9759 				}
9760 
9761 				elem = elem[dir];
9762 			}
9763 
9764 			checkSet[i] = match;
9765 		}
9766 	}
9767 }
9768 
9769 function dirCheck( dir, cur, doneName, checkSet, nodeCheck, isXML ) {
9770 	for ( var i = 0, l = checkSet.length; i < l; i++ ) {
9771 		var elem = checkSet[i];
9772 
9773 		if ( elem ) {
9774 			var match = false;
9775 			
9776 			elem = elem[dir];
9777 
9778 			while ( elem ) {
9779 				if ( elem.sizcache === doneName ) {
9780 					match = checkSet[elem.sizset];
9781 					break;
9782 				}
9783 
9784 				if ( elem.nodeType === 1 ) {
9785 					if ( !isXML ) {
9786 						elem.sizcache = doneName;
9787 						elem.sizset = i;
9788 					}
9789 
9790 					if ( typeof cur !== "string" ) {
9791 						if ( elem === cur ) {
9792 							match = true;
9793 							break;
9794 						}
9795 
9796 					} else if ( Sizzle.filter( cur, [elem] ).length > 0 ) {
9797 						match = elem;
9798 						break;
9799 					}
9800 				}
9801 
9802 				elem = elem[dir];
9803 			}
9804 
9805 			checkSet[i] = match;
9806 		}
9807 	}
9808 }

9826 Sizzle.isXML = function( elem ) {
9827 	// documentElement is verified for cases where it doesn't yet exist
9828 	// (such as loading iframes in IE - #4833) 
9829 	var documentElement = (elem ? elem.ownerDocument || elem : 0).documentElement;
9830 
9831 	return documentElement ? documentElement.nodeName !== "HTML" : false;
9832 };

9834 var posProcess = function( selector, context ) {
9835 	var match,
9836 		tmpSet = [],
9837 		later = "",
9838 		root = context.nodeType ? [context] : context;
9839 
9840 	// Position selectors must be done after the filter
9841 	// And so must :not(positional) so we move all PSEUDOs to the end
9842 	while ( (match = Expr.match.PSEUDO.exec( selector )) ) {
9843 		later += match[0];
9844 		selector = selector.replace( Expr.match.PSEUDO, "" );
9845 	}
9846 
9847 	selector = Expr.relative[selector] ? selector + "*" : selector;
9848 
9849 	for ( var i = 0, l = root.length; i < l; i++ ) {
9850 		Sizzle( selector, root[i], tmpSet );
9851 	}
9852 
9853 	return Sizzle.filter( later, tmpSet );
9854 };
